title: coconut icing cake
directions: Mix the
sugar,
coconut
and sour cream and set aside. Prepare cake as directed on box.
When done, take a string and divide each layer in half, making 4 layers.
Put icing between each layer and
on top.
Place in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: hanover beans
directions: Cook Great Northern beans until done.
Put all together and cook a little longer.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate at least 8 hours. Serve with crackers.

title: sweet and sour meatballs with cabbage
directions: Combine cranberry sauce and tomato sauce in 4 to 5-quart pot over low heat.
Combine beef, salt, pepper, garlic powder, egg and bread crumbs.
Form into meatballs and put into pot of cranberry and tomato sauce.
(It's not necessary to brown meatballs.)
Put cabbage on top.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: two-day cucumber pickles
directions: Dissolve lime in water, stir well.
Soak cucumbers in lime solution 24 hours.
Remove from lime and wash about 4 times until all grit is gone.
Put spices in cheese cloth bag, place in bottom of jar.
Put cucumbers on top of spices.
Mix vinegar, sugar and salt until dissolved and pour over cucumbers.
Soak overnight. Boil cucumbers, spices and liquid until change in color, 20 to 25 minutes.
Put in hot jars with hot lids.
Process 10 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Spread. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Batter will be thick.

title: no peek stew
directions: Put
ingredients
in a 2 1/2 quart casserole and cover. Bake at
300° for 3 hours.
Do not peek.
Let stand 30 minutes before serving.
Can
be
served with cooked rice or noodles. Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into celery pieces.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight.
Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except butter. Pour into large baking dish. Melt butter and pour over top. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until golden brown.

title: curried chicken
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and marinate the chicken for 1 hour.
Grill or broil chicken for 5 to 10 minutes per side.

title: dieter's corn bread
directions: Combine ingredients with wire whisk.
Pour batter into greased muffin tins or skillet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until brown.
You will think you are eating real corn bread.

title: peanut butter fudge(ice cream topping)
directions: Combine Hershey's syrup and peanut butter.
Add evaporated milk until spooning consistency.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Heat 1 cup pear juice and pour over jello.
Cream the cheese with 2 tablespoons milk.
Mash pears.
Whip jello when partially set.
Whip the cream; add cheese, pears and jello.
Pour into mold.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put it in a loaf pan. Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes or until center is done. Drain off the fat. Let set for 5 minutes before serving.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Lightly grease large baking dish.
Place pork chops flat in dish.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over pork chops. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake another 5 to 10 minutes or just enough to firm up top. Serves 6.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix together and roll out flat and make donut shape you want. Fry in hot grease until brown.

title: easy oven chicken
directions: Mix corn flakes, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken in Pet milk and then corn flake mixture.
Grease flat pan; spread out chicken.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chinatown chops
directions: In large skillet, brown pork chops.
Remove to plate.
Brown Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Stir in 2 cups hot water, can of mushrooms (undrained) and contents of vegetable sauce envelope from Rice-A-Roni package.
Place browned chops on top.
Sprinkle with soy sauce.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pound cake cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients together. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Put pecan on top of cookie before baking.

title: aunt clara's corn pudding
directions: Combine corn and eggs.
Stir in milk, cream and butter.
Add green pepper, pimiento and onion.
Mix well.
Blend in sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set in a pan of hot water.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple pickles
directions: Cut pineapple into 1/4-inch sticks.
Combine all ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars and process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: crock pot macaroni
directions: Spray crockpot with non-stick spray.
Mix ingredients and pour in.
Cook 3 hours on low.
Do not overcook, it will firm after it is turned off.

title: roast pork
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook pork loin roast, fat side up, for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle generously with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Roast for first half hour uncovered.
Pour dill pickle juice or pickled cabbage in jar over roast.
Flip roast once.
Cook slow and long.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly saute caps in butter.
Arrange on cookie sheet and set aside.
Brown sausage and drain off grease.
Mix sausage and cream cheese until smooth. Fill mushroom caps. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes.
(May be made a day before and refrigerated.)

title: potato salad(chunky)
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks and boil until tender.
Drain water off potatoes.
Chop onion, bread and butter pickles and drained tomatoes into potatoes.
Add salt and black pepper to taste.
Add Miracle Whip to consistency desired.
Do not mash or beat potatoes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix oleo, oil and sugar well.
Add eggs, vanilla, baking soda, cream of tartar and flour.
Roll into balls and flatten with fork on greased cookie sheet.

title: party 7 layer salad
directions: In a small bowl combine mayonnaise, sour cream, milk and mustard.
Stir until smooth.
Place salad greens in bottom of large glass bowl.
Layer with ham, cheese, mostaccioli, onion and peas. Spread mayonnaise mixture evenly over peas.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap; chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Toss just before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: jamaica junk
directions: Brown the sausage, onion, pepper and celery together until sausage is thoroughly cooked.
Mix the soup and hot water together. Add all the other ingredients.
Bake in a deep casserole dish, covered, 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss cream steak
directions: Cut meat into serving portions; dust with salt, pepper and flour.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add onions and saute until golden.
Remove from pan.
Melt remaining butter.
Add meat and brown on both sides.
Combine onions and remaining ingredients. Add to steak.
Transfer to casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: kratzete (scratcher)
directions: Mix 8 tablespoons of flour with milk, salt and eggs.
Dough should be like our biscuit dough.
Heat oil in pan and make dough about size of a walnut; shake pan until dough is golden brown.

title: philadelphia cream cheese mints
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Roll in balls the size of marbles or press into rose or leaf design molds.
Place one side in granulated sugar and with sugar side down, press into mold.
Unmold at once and place on waxed paper.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and onions in large stone jar; combine water and salt.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 3 hours.
Then drain well, combine other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Remove from heat and stir until cucumbers are hot through. Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, add a few drops of coloring.
Use paper cup liners in muffin pan.
Fill pan almost full, freeze.
Store in plastic bag.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (except the coconut) in blender, on low speed.
Grease pie plate.
Pour mixture into pie plate and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in milk, butter, nutmeg and vanilla; pour into dry ingredients and mix just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups two-thirds full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Brush tops with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Yield:
1 dozen.

title: one dish meal
directions: Slice the onion in bottom of a large casserole. Put the other ingredients in layers over the onion.
Pour the tomatoes over the top.
Place strips of bacon on top of the tomatoes.
Cook, covered, 2 hours at 300°.
Uncover and cook 30 minutes.
Makes a great Sunday dinner.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Combine spinach and next 6 ingredients.
Stir until blended. Lay out 2 sheets phyllo, one on top of other.
Brush top with melted butter.
Spread about 3 to 4 tablespoons spinach mixture long shorter edge of phyllo.
Roll up twice.
Fold in sides and continue rolling jelly roll fashion.

title: pepper steak
directions: Combine flour and seasonings.
Pound into meat with meat hammer or edge of heavy saucer.
In skillet, brown meat in shortening and pour off fat.
Add soup and ketchup.
Cover.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour.
Add green pepper.
Cook 20 minutes more or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Serve with mashed potatoes. Makes 4 servings.

title: kathy's sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in lasagna pan.
Remove from freezer 1/2 hour before serving.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and chips.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop filling by teaspoonfuls in an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: chili con carne
directions: In an 8-inch skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients except beans.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat; cook, uncovered, about 30 minutes.
Stir in beans (with liquid); heat until bubbly.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Slice crust from bread.
Cut bread in finger strips and cover peaches.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine yolks, milk and oil.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Spoon 1/2 cup portions on preheated waffle iron.

title: monster cookies
directions: Use ice cream scoop to form balls, flatten gently on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
Put half and half and water in top of double boiler.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Add cooked, chopped broccoli.
Mix cornstarch and water in small bowl.
Stir into cheese mixture and cook until soup thickens.
Makes 10 (1 cup) servings.

title: brownies
directions: Melt the caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Set aside. Mix the cake mix, butter or margarine and 1/3 cup evaporated milk and place half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with the nuts and chocolate chips.
Drizzle the caramel mixture on top.
Pour remaining batter over this mixture and bake 20 minutes at 300°.
If batter is too stiff, add a little more milk.

title: chocolate pecan cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl until creamy.
Blend in egg. Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add to cream mixture.
Gradually stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Boil for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes; take off stove.
Add peanut butter until melted. Mix oats in well (don't stir too long, because it will get too hard).
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Early in the day:
In a large, uncovered saucepan over medium heat in 1 inch of boiling water, cook potatoes with skins on with 1 teaspoon of salt for 20 to 30 minutes until potatoes are fork-tender; drain and chill.
About 1 hour before serving, preheat oven to 375°.
Peel and dice potatoes.

title: vegetable frittata
directions: Lay the pancetta slices in a cast-iron skillet and cook over low heat until crisp.
Remove from the pan and crumble.
Cut the vegetable in pieces and place in the skillet.
Cook over medium heat in the oil until it begins to wilt. Season with salt and pepper and mix with the eggs and bacon in a bowl.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir until melted.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper. Let harden.
Store in airtight container.

title: ham & garlic pork rolls
directions: Lay the ham on top of the pounded cutlets. In a small bowl, combine eggs and water, beating to make an egg
wash. In another shallow bowl, put in the bread crumbs. In a large saute pan, heat enough oil to come 1/2 inch up the sides of the pan.

title: mini-chicken pizza melt
directions: Lay out opened hamburger buns on cookie sheet and spread each with heaping tablespoonful of the spaghetti sauce.
Divide the chicken pieces evenly over the sauce.
Add vegetables, if desired. Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake about 10 minutes at 350° to melt and brown cheese. Serve warm.

title: molly's brownies
directions: Grease and flour oblong cake pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Do not use electric mixer; just stir by hand with wooden spoon.
Add ingredients in order given.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: herbed rolled flounder
directions: Lay fillets, smooth side down.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of parsley, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Roll up each from wide end; secure with a wooden pick.

title: 6 - 8 week muffins
directions: Mix bran, sugar, flour, salt and soda in very large bowl.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk; mix well.
Store in covered container. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Freeze overnight.
Limeade can be substituted.
Garnish with lemon or lime wedges.

title: cola salad
directions: Heat 1 Coca-Cola and mix with Jell-O.
Dissolve well, then add other Coca-Cola, mixing thoroughly.
Add pineapple and chopped pecans.
Chill according to Jell-O directions.

title: brown rim cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add salt, flour and nuts.
Hand roll into small balls.
Press with bottom of glass (flat and floured).
Bake until rim of cookie is brown.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: goulash
directions: Saute onion with a little cooking oil.
Add meat and cook until done.
Drain excess grease from meat.
Add tomato soup and sauce. Swish can with some hot water and pour in also.
Cook macaroni in separate pan until done.
Drain macaroni and add to meat mixture. Stir.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mmmmm, Mmmmm good!
It's best to serve this with fried potatoes and onions.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Save enough whipping cream and cherries to spread on top of mixture.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar and cooled water to form a syrup.
Dissolve instant coffee in 1 cup boiling water and add to syrup.
Pour in 1-quart vodka when syrup is well mixed and not too hot.
Split vanilla bean in half, lengthwise.
Put vanilla bean in bottom of a half gallon jug.
Fill with mixture and let stand, capped, at room temperature for 2 weeks.

title: my favorite ice cream
directions: Mix together in freezer can.
Might need to add sugar depending on sweetness of fruit.
Freeze with ice cream freezer. Makes 4 quarts.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter; boil 1 minute.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonful on a buttered dish.

title: rich chocolate fudge
directions: Combine chocolate and cream and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add sugar and salt; stir until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils.
Cook without stirring until small amount of mixture forms a soft ball in cold water (236°).
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla without stirring.
Cool to lukewarm (110°), then beat until creamy.
Add nuts and turn at once into buttered pan.
When firm, cut into squares.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add pepper, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Drain. Add tomatoes soup, undiluted.

title: sherry shake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Add cubes and blend.

title: oven beef burgundy
directions: Preheat oven to 275°. Cut beef into large cubes and put in roaster; do not brown. Add layers of carrots, onion, green pepper and mushrooms. Mix tapioca, bread crumbs, allspice, salt, pepper, tomatoes and wine together in separate bowl and pour over beef. Cover tightly and bake for 3 hours at 275° or until meat is tender. Serve with rice or noodles. Serves 8.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a large crock pot or a big soup pot.
The longer it cooks the better it taste.
Top with sour cream and grated cheese.

title: meat sauce for spaghetti
directions: Brown beef until almost done; add sage, garlic, cloves, marjoram, Worcestershire, water and onions.
Mix together then add salt, bay leaves, chili powder, salt, tomato paste and mushrooms (optional).
Cook for 1 hour on low heat.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams; reserve juice.
Fry out enough fatback to produce grease to saute onions (oil or bacon fat may be substituted). Discard meat and saute onions for about 5 minutes or until cooked clear.
Add enough water or juice to measure 4 cups liquid.
Mix liquids, potatoes and onions together.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Taste test for seasoning.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 quarts. Freezes well, but be sure not to boil when reheating.

title: chocolate peanut hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt the ingredients together either in microwave or over hot water on stove.
Stir and serve over ice cream or use as icing for cake.

title: sour cream mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes as to mash.
Mash and blend ingredients.
Put in flat buttered baking dish.
Put about 3 pats of margarine on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jezabel sauce
directions: Mix all together and serve over cream cheese with your favorite cracker or triscuits.

title: granny's old fashioned corn meal berry cake
directions: Mix together well the corn meal, sugar, flour and salt.
To that dry mixture add the milk, eggs and margarine.
Add berries and pour into a well-greased, corn meal sprinkled iron skillet. Bake at 375° until done.

title: baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Put cheese slices over chicken.
Mix soup and sherry; pour over cheese.
Mix herb dressing with butter or oleo; spread over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: super juicy hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pat into hamburger patties (or can be shaped into a meat loaf).
Place hamburgers in a warm frying pan and fry with moderate heat until done.
Can also bake in a 350° oven approximately 20 minutes on each side.
If baking as a meat loaf, cook for 45 minutes at same temperature.

title: chocolate refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening until fluffy.
Add vanilla and sugars; beat until creamy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add chocolate; mix well. Combine remaining ingredients and add; mixing well.
Chill for several hours.
Roll out to
1/8-inch thick and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375°.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch dish or two 8 x 8-inch baking dishes with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread processed beans onto bottom of prepared pan.

title: whipped cream white cake
directions: Whip sweet cream and beat egg whites.
Combine and add salt and water.
Mix together.
Then add sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder into mixture.
Bake in layer cake pans at 350° for minutes.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and cook until it spins a long thread.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Pour syrup slowly over egg whites while beating. Beat until a little in a spoon will hold its shape on wax paper.
Work fast as the candy sets up fast.
Put half a pecan on each piece, if desired.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: In electric blender combine 1 tomato, half the cucumber, half the onion, a quarter of green pepper, the pimiento and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Blend.
Cover and mix at high speed, 30 seconds to puree the vegetables.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; add cut up oranges.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: shrimp and rice salad(servings:  4)
directions: Cook rice and let cool.
Add scallions, shrimp, mayonnaise, ginger, lemon juice and salt.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Cool in refrigerator several hours if desired.
Serve at room temperature, sprinkled with sesame seed and surrounded by snow peas on a large platter or shallow bowl.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix butter, spaghetti, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Make "crust" in buttered pie pan with mixture.
Spread cottage cheese on top.
Cook hamburger, onion, green pepper and spaghetti sauce. Spread over cottage cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Put Parmesan cheese on top and bake until melted.

title: quick 'n easy mushroom quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter; add lemon juice.
When mushrooms are slightly browned, add heavy cream, eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serve hot!!

title: egg-drop soup
directions: Combine bouillon cubes and hot water.
Add seasonings, sugar and oleo in pan.
Blend cornstarch and cold water.
Stir into boiling soup.

title: green bean delight
directions: Into buttered casserole, place green beans (drained), salt and pepper.
Cover with cream soup.
Top with onions and bake at 350° until bubbly and brown on top, about 45 minutes.

title: stuffed pork tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Slit tenderloin lengthwise, but don't cut completely through.
Mix the next 6 ingredients together and fill tenderloin.
Tie with cord and wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake 1 hour.
Fold back foil and bake an additional 30 minutes or until meat is browned and tender.
Serves 4.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together and pour over potatoes and eggs.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add syrup, sugar, butter, salt and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Stir in rolled oats and pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes until center is firm and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: spicy baked chicken
directions: Discard skin from chicken and place pieces in a shallow baking dish.
Combine and thoroughly mix remaining ingredients.
Brush mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, basting frequently until tender.
Chicken may be placed under broiler 5 minutes for additional browning.

title: barley casserole
directions: Soak barley covered by water 8 hours.
Cook barley 3/4 hour or until tender.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Blend in blender all ingredients except pork chops.
Cut up pork chops and take out all bones and fry.
Pour off grease and add sauce.
Simmer for 15 to 30 minutes (add more water if it cooks down too much).
Serve with rice, refried beans and tortillas.

title: poppy seed bread or cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: sweet and sour shells salad
directions: Cook shells, not too soft.
Mix together to form a dressing: soup, vinegar, oil and sugar.
Pour all but 1 cup of dressing on noodle/vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, pour other cup of dressing over shells and mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Dissolve sugar in milk over low heat.
Bring to a boil and cook to soft ball stage (230 degrees approx.).
Remove from heat and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 8 inch or 9 inch pan.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Cut into squares. Store in air tight container.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Note:
Directions are for a high wattage oven.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the meat over low heat. Drain. Stir in beans, chili powder, salt and 2/3 cup Catalina dressing.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: shrimp with lemon and fresh basil
directions: Combine water, salt, bay leaf and lemon slices in saucepan over high heat.
Simmer 3 minutes, then add shrimp.
Cook on low heat until shrimp are pink throughout.
Drain off water, allow shrimp to cool.
Peel, leaving tails intact, and devein.
Set aside.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Spread mixture evenly on 1 side of each ham slice.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Cover and chill well.
Carefully slice each roll into half-inch pieces.
Serve with toothpicks.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: m.e.'s chicken breasts
directions: Drain small can of mushrooms.
Add chopped onion, soy sauce, honey and catsup.
Mix.
Pour over chicken breasts in flat pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate mixture and beat until smooth.
Fold chocolate mixture into Cool Whip; blend until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours. Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: chex party mix
directions: In 15 x 10 x 2-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven. Remove.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire.
Gradually add cereal, nuts, raisins and pretzels.
Stir until all pieces are evenly coated.

title: "the best brownies"
directions: Stir together butter and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well with a spoon.
Stir in flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; beat until well blended.
If desired, stir in nuts.

title: potato cheese casserole(crock-pot)
directions: Mix
thoroughly
and pour into greased crock-pot.
Bake on High about 3 to 4 hours.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Cover bottom of 9 X 13 pan with rice, pat out evenly. Layer chicken on top of rice. Next, layer frozen vegetables on top of chicken. In a separate bowl, mix soup, 2 cups water, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Pour on top of layers, covering evenly. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop lettuce, tomato and onion.
Add kidney beans to salad, then add grated cheese.
Crumble Fritos over all and toss with dressing.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Pour melted butter over crushed cookies and mix together. Spread 1/2 of mixture in pan and place in refrigerator for 20 minutes.
(Save 1/2 of mixture for topping.)
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 Cool Whip and confectioners sugar.
Spread over cookie crust.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk into batter.
Place partially melted butter in bottom of baking dish.
Pour batter over butter.
Pour peaches on top of batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Can be served hot with vanilla ice cream.
If served with ice cream, makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg; mix well. Add mixed dry ingredients and milk (dough will be thick).
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes, then press marshmallows (cut side down) on top.
Bake 2 minutes more.
Cool and frost with chocolate icing.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and fruit-flavored yogurt together.
Pour into crust.
Slice strawberries, bananas or fruit of your choice on top.
Refrigerate 3 hours; do not freeze.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Place paper cupcake liners in muffin tins.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of mixture in each liner.
Pat down.
Place cream cheese, vanilla, 3/4 cup sugar and eggs in mixing bowl or food processor.
Mix or process until well blended.
(Mixture should be very smooth. Pour on top of crumbs, filling about 1/2 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325° or until lightly browned.
When cool, top with prepared pie filling of your choice.

title: dried beef 'n onion dip
directions: Dice beef and onion.
Mix enough dill pickle juice to cream cheese to make it manageable and then add the diced beef and onion.
Form into ball.
Chill.
Serve with sesame crackers.

title: barbecue pork chops(crock-pot)
directions: Brown pork chops over medium heat about 5 minutes per side. Place brown pork chops in slow cooker. Pour barbecue sauce over top. Cook on low.

title: nana's apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine lemon juice and apples.
In medium bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Pour dry ingredients over apples and toss until coated.
Pour mixture into 1 pie crust.
Top with the other pie crust.
Cut slits into top of pie crust.
Dip finger into milk and dab onto the top crust.
Seal crust along edges.

title: paella ole
directions: Cook and stir shrimp and garlic in butter in skillet until shrimp turn pink.
Mix broth and cornstarch together and stir into shrimp.
Add tomatoes, pepperoni and vegetables.
Cook and stir until mix thickens and comes to a full boil.
Stir in rice and saffron.
Cover and remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff. Makes 4 servings.

title: oriental submarine sandwich
directions: Cut beef into thin strips.
Panfry or broil 3 to 4 minutes each side while warming rolls.
Makes 3 (6 to 8-inch sandwiches.)

title: chocolate fudge cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs, cocoa, 1 teaspoon instant coffee and milk with mixer until smooth.
Add flour, salt, oil, soda, chocolate bits and rolled oats and mix with spoon.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cuban potato salad
directions: Cook the potatoes.
After they have cooled, cut them into slices.
Place the onion slices and green pepper over the potato slices.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Add oil and vinegar dressing; toss lightly.
Refrigerate for at least two hours before serving.
Serves eight.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes into bottom of baking dish.
Add layer of sausage in patties or slices.
Peel and slice apples over top.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Cover.
Bake one hour at 375°.
Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and beat well.
Stir in pecans and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: caramel pie
directions: *To caramelize sugar, place 3/4 cup sugar in heavy iron skillet (smallest size).
Stir over medium heat until sugar melts and begins to brown.
Cook to desired color and remove from heat immediately.

title: impress your date chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter or margarine; drain.
Mix gravy mix with wine instead of water.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle mushrooms and artichoke hearts over all.
Simmer 1/2 hour, turning once or twice.
Serve with rice.

title: grandma's irish soda bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add butter and rub until like meal.
Add buttermilk and mix all.
Knead on floured board until smooth. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Makes one loaf.

title: fruit salad
directions: Make pudding as directed using 1 1/2 cups fruit juice from pineapple.
Let cool.
Fold into fruit.
Add fresh bananas. Refrigerate.

title: chicken with rice casserole
directions: Melt butter; add soups.
Heat, then add rice and heat together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken breasts over rice mixture.
Pour additional 1/4 cup melted butter over breasts. Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: pink squirrel fondue
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in boiler.
Add Marshmallow Creme and heat slowly until warm.
Serve warm in fondue pot or chafing dish.
Use for dipping fresh strawberries.

title: first prize cake
directions: Mix together; beat 4 minutes.
Pour into two 9-inch round or 13 x 9-inch pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: beef 'n beans dinner
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet; drain off fat and put in crock-pot.	Brown onions and bacon; drain off fat.	Add bacon, onions and	remaining ingredients to pot.
Stir together well. Cover and cook 4 to 6 hours.
Delicious on a cold winter day.

title: chocolate float
directions: Bring to a boil and pour into 2-quart casserole dish 1 cup sugar and water.

title: vegetable salsa
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate. Best if served after 12 to 24 hours. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: red sparkle punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine drink mix and sugar.
Add water and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add limeade; mix well.
Chill. Just before serving, gradually stir in lemon-lime soda.
Add ice cubes and garnish with lemon and lime slices.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving pieces.
Pound seasoned flour into steak.
Brown steak on both sides in shortening.
Add water; cover; cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Uncover; cook down excess liquid.
Pour in soup; heat slowly.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole. Cook zucchini and onion in a little water until tender.
Put on top of butter.
Mix dressing as on box.
Put on top of onion and zucchini.
Add sour cream, soup and 1/2 stick margarine on top. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cut crusts off bread and cut into small cubes.
Cut cheese into bite size pieces.
Place 1/3 of shrimp in casserole.
Top with 1/3 of bread cubes and 1/3 of cheese cubes.
Repeat 2 more times.
Pour butter over all.
Combine eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Pour over all.
Cover and stand overnight or 3 hours.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sole provencal
directions: In a large skillet slowly saute onion and celery in oil until tender.
Add tomatoes (put in blender very briefly), parsley, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer gently for 20 minutes. Add sole and continue cooking for 10 to 15 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: veal brawn
directions: Divide the shoulder into two; rinse the shin and crack the bones if necessary.
Put the meat into a pot.
Add the water and bring slowly to a boil.
Skim off the scum.
Add the seasoning and onion and boil until the meat comes off the bone.
This takes about one hour.
Remove the meat and strain the liquid.

title: easy baked potato soup
directions: Peel and dice the baked potatoes; set aside.
In a Dutch oven or soup kettle, cook the bacon over medium heat until crisp.
Using a slotted spoon, remove to paper towels.
Drain, reserving 1 1/2 teaspoons dripping.
Add the soups, milk, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce, onion powder, pepper, liquid smoke (if desired) and reserved potatoes to the drippings.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally. Stir in sour cream; cook for 1 to 2 minutes or until heated through (do not boil).
Garnish with cheddar cheese and bacon.
Serves 10.

title: fat-free white cake
directions: Spray a 9-inch pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
In a medium bowl, mix egg whites, milk, corn syrup and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire racks.
Makes 16 servings.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Place shredded cabbage in a very large bowl; sprinkle with sugar.
Toss just until mixed.
Cover.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Freeze for 45 minutes.
Stir and pour.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Slice potatoes thinly.
Place potatoes in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Place pork chops on top of potatoes.
Mix soup with water.
Pour this mixture over potatoes and pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aunt mae's watergate sin cake
directions: Cake:
Beat eggs, oil and juice of oranges together.
Add cake mix and beat 3 minutes.
Fold in oranges and bake at 350° for 28 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center of cake comes out clean.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry cheese tarts
directions: Cream the cheese; add eggs and sugar and beat until smooth. In a small muffin pan, place muffin liners.
Place a vanilla wafer.
Fill with cheese mixture until 3/4 full.
Bake in muffin pans for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
When full, top each cake with a tablespoon of cherry filling.

title: meatless chili
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rice, in an 8-quart stock pot. Bring to a boil.
Reduce to medium heat and cook, partially covered, for 3 to 3 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: endive dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and serve over endive.

title: rich's mother's modified chili
directions: Brown ground beef in large pot.
Drain off any fat.
Over medium heat, add tomatoes and remaining ingredients, stirring after each addition.
Add the kidney beans last.
After mixture begins to bubble, turn heat to low and simmer for 30-40 minutes.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour into hot iron skillet. Cook in 450° oven for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong 9x13x2 inch pan.
Mix all ingredients, adding zucchini last.
Spread gently in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: deviled eggs divan
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise; remove yolks.
Mash yolks; stir in next 3 ingredients.
Spoon into egg white halves.
In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Stir in flour and next 3 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Stir in cheese until melted. Remove from heat.
Spread half of sauce in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange cooked asparagus alternately with deviled egg halves in diagonal rows in dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over asparagus.
Bake in 400° oven 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix milk and oats.
Allow to stand 5 minutes. Add all other ingredients and mix. Cook on hot griddle like regular pancakes. Serve with butter and syrup. Serves 4.

title: famous amish funnel cakes
directions: To beaten eggs add milk and sugar.
In separate bowl sift dry ingredients.
Add egg mixture beating until smooth.
Heat oil to 375°.
Pour batter into hot oil through a regular funnel.
Control the flow of the batter by holding your finger on the bottom of the funnel.
Make patterns, designs or whatever with the stream of batter as it flows into the hot oil.
When cakes are golden brown, drain on paper towels and sprinkle with confectioners sugar and serve warm.

title: talirino casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add another 1/4 pound shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until hot and bubbly.
Can be made ahead of time and kept in freezer.

title: homemade play doh
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat over medium heat until it leaves side of pan.
Remove.
Add food coloring.
Knead until soft and pliable.
Be careful not to burn hands and store in a plastic bag.
Has no odor like commercial play doh and can be swept up if it dries on carpet.
Have fun.
Do not eat!

title: egg custard pie
directions: Use unbaked pie shell.
Put into refrigerator while mixing pie filling.

title: spinach and tomato casserole
directions: Mix together and put into casserole.
Top with 2 alternate layers of fresh sliced tomatoes, salt and pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Top with heavy layer of cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook all 40 minutes.
Pour into casserole.
Cover with shredded cheese (I use pizza cheese).
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or cook in crock-pot and add cheese 15 minutes before serving.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together, mixing well.
Chill before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: garlic fried chicken
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; mix well.
Place chicken in a shallow pan and pour sour cream mixture over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove chicken from liquid.
Dredge chicken in flour.
Heat 1-inch of oil in a large skillet to 325°; add chicken and fry 15 to 20 minutes, turning once.
Drain chicken well on paper towels.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse kidney beans. Add celery, onion, eggs and pickles.
Mix with enough salad dressing to your taste.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix ingredients in casserole dish.
Add 3 cups boiling water. Cover and cook in oven at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Cook the peas, carrots, celery, onions, cabbage, zucchini, chicken broth and butter for 20 minutes.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Cook 15 minutes more.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Combine yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, flour, milk, water, coconut and salt in a medium saucepan.
Blend thoroughly. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until thickened. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and butter.
Spoon mixture into pastry shell.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar and cream of tartar.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread meringue over pie, begin careful to seal edges. Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish. In a small bowl, combine picante sauce, brown sugar and mustard. Pour over chicken. Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes. Serve over rice. 4 servings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Grease large bowl.
Heat milk, water and butter in a saucepan until very warm (120° to 130°).
Combine 2 cups of flour, sugar, salt and yeast in mixing bowl.
Add heated mixture and egg.
Beat with electric mixer on high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn dough onto floured board.
Cover with mixing bowl. Let set 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Form ball with dough and place in greased bowl.
Turn once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place, free from draft, until double in bulk, about 45 minutes.

title: preserve cookie bars
directions: Cream sugar and margarine, then add dry ingredients.
Press half in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add preserves, then sprinkle remaining mixture over top.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together first five ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate two hours.
Makes five cups.

title: fruit shakes
directions: Mix 1/4 cup each of milk and orange juice with 1/2 banana, honey and a dash of vanilla in blender.

title: cranbrosia
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Mix thoroughly to dissolve sugar.
Drain well and reserve liquid from oranges and pineapple. Add oranges, pineapple and coconut to cranberries; sprinkle gelatin over 3/4 cup of combined juices to soften.
Place over medium heat, stirring constantly to dissolve gelatin.
Add to fruits.
Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese bake(makes 5 servings)
directions: Bring water to a boil in medium sized saucepan; add the 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt.
Add elbow macaroni and boil for 10 minutes or until slightly soft.

title: pizza bread
directions: Let bread rise per package instructions.
Grind pepperoni and mix with rest of ingredients.
Roll out each bread loaf.
Place 1/2 of pepperoni/cheese mix down center of each flat rolled out dough.
Fold edges of dough over mixture and pinch edges together, sealing mix inside.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with warm spaghetti sauce.

title: joan's chicken with rice
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in rice, onion flakes,
salt, water and soup.
Place chicken
pieces
on
top mixture.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake, uncovered,
at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: one dish chicken and rice bake
directions: In 2-quart shallow baking dish, mix ingredients.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle with additional paprika and pepper.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until chicken and rice are done.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt oleo, set aside to cool slightly.
Mix together, eggs, syrup, salt, sugar and vanilla.
Add cooled oleo.
Mix flour with pecans.
Add to first mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° about 40 to 50 minutes until set.
The center will be slightly soft.

title: cream cheese and olive spread
directions: Mix together.
Chill and serve with an assortment of crackers.

title: jellied cucumber salad
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients and set aside.
Mix last 4 ingredients well; mix with Jell-O well.
Pour into salad mold or any container (depending on whether you plan to slice or spoon out servings).
Refrigerate until jelled.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Combine
sugar, milk and butter.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly,
until	it
boils
at
240° or until mixture forms semi-firm ball in cold water.
Remove from heat, add dates and nuts.
Stir
until	thickens.
Roll into 2 rolls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in damp cloth until firm.
Slice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat eggs, margarine and sugar at least 20 minutes (very important)!

Slice 3 bananas - dip in lemon juice -place on crumb crust. Spread one 12 oz well drained crushed pineapple over the bananas. Pour egg mixture on top. Cover with one large container of cool whip. Drizzle with Hershey syrup. Sprinkle with chopped nuts - add cherries. Chill several hours.

title: country crust bread
directions: Mix; knead. Let rise. Divide; put in greased loaf pans and let rise again. Bake in 370° oven for 35 minutes. Turn out on wire rack and grease with margarine.

title: pastry hearts
directions: Soften margarine and mix by hand the flour, cottage cheese and vanilla.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out dough on floured surface to 1/4 to 1/2-inch.
Cut hearts out with cookie cutter and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Pour butter over stuffing mix.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Mix broccoli and corn in baking dish.
Mix in 1/2 cup stuffing mix. Cover the mix with other stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
One egg may be added if desired.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda in a large mixing bowl.
In a second large mixing bowl, cream sugars and oil, then add eggs to this mixture and beat well.
Add dry ingredients to the batter mixture alternating with buttermilk. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water, corn syrup and salt.
Loosely cover and microwave 5 to 6 minutes or until boiling.
Uncover.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes or until hard ball stage is reached.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly pour hot syrup over egg whites while beating at high speed.
Add vanilla and continue to beat 4 to 5 minutes or until it holds its shape.
Fold in nuts.
Drop teaspoons of candy onto waxed paper.

title: darlene's pinwheels
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except tortillas.
Spread mixture evenly over tortillas and roll as tightly as possible. Wrap in foil or plastic wrap and chill for 3 hours.
Unwrap, slice and serve with salsa.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; beat in eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in moderate oven about 45 minutes. This makes one pie.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes (as if to mash). Drain.
Add Miracle Whip and onion salt; sprinkle chopped peppers and crispy bacon (broken into pieces) on top.
Pour 1/4 cup hot grease and pepper juice over the top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy one dish ham bake
directions: Mix broccoli, soups and milk together.
Add ham and mix well. Pour into 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixing bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; then stir in chips and nuts (batter will be stiff).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets, about 2 inches apart. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Spread slices of beef on bottom of baking dish.
Place seasoned (salted and peppered) chicken wrapped in bacon on top of beef.
Mix sour cream with mushroom soup and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover to brown.

title: joan's famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
For variety, add chopped nutmeats, raisins, chocolate chips, coconut and M&M's.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: clam chowder
directions: Put all of the above in a crockpot.
Add 2 pints half and half and 1 can minced clams.
Stir well.
Cook on low.
Stir occasionally.
Cook until creamy, about 2 hours or more.

title: shrimp baskets
directions: Spear both ends of a shrimp on a toothpick, pressing the ends as closely together as possible without breaking shrimp.
Combine remaining ingredients and fill "basket" (formed by shrimp on pick).
Makes 8 servings.

title: grandma penney's turkey and dressing
directions: (May need to double recipe.)

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello and water until dissolved.
Add pineapple, orange slices and orange juice.
Stir well.
Refrigerate until set.
Mix lemon pudding and 1 cup milk.
Add Cool Whip and spread on top of jello.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: heavenly lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Mash cream cheese. Add hot Jell-O and mix slowly.
Stir until dissolved.
Melt marshmallows in 1/4 cup boiling water in top of double boiler, then add Jell-O mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups of cold water.
Add Cool Whip and beat mixture until it is smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts. Pour into greased mold or large baking dish.
Chill until set.

title: hamburgers parmigiana
directions: In a bowl, combine well the beef, crumbs, egg and 1/3 cup of the Parmesan cheese. Divide into 4 parts. Shape into patties. Heat oil in heavy skillet. Add meat patties.
Brown over high heat 1 minute on each side.
Place into a shallow baking dish. Add onion to drippings in skillet.
Cook on low heat 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, oregano and tomato sauce. Simmer 5 minutes. Sprinkle 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese over meat patties. Top with the tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and Mozzarella cheeses. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until sauce is bubbly and meat is cooked.
Serve on top of toasted, buttered bread.
Garnish with lettuce and olives.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Roll out half the dough at a time to 1/8-inch thick.
Use a pizza cutter to cut into desired shapes and sizes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 375°.
Turn off heat and leave biscuits in oven until cool.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Simmer ingredients for 15 minutes.
Lay pork chops in dish and pour mixture over.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: puffed rice squares
directions: Boil sugars and Karo.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over the puffed rice.
Put in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan and flatten it out. Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: finger paint
directions: You will also need baby food jars or jars with screw on lids. Mix cornstarch with water and boil until mixture thickens.
Cool. Pour into containers and add food coloring.
Mix and screw on lids.

title: lemon filling(for meringue)
directions: Beat egg yolks and whole egg together until light.
Add one cup sugar.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to mixed flour and salt.
Continue beating until well blended.
Gradually pour boiling water, stir constantly.
Add lemon juice.
Cook in top of double boiler until thick.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Add butter and cool.
Fill shells.

title: boston cream pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender or food processor with steel blade in place.
Process for 30 seconds, until all ingredients are blended.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain. Add taco seasoning and French dressing. Store in fridge overnight. Add rest when ready to go.

title: ham and cheese crescents
directions: Separate crescent roll dough into triangles.
Place a thin slice of ham and a thin slice of cheese on top of each triangle. Roll up and place on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and
sugar
well.
Add eggs one at a time. Add orange juice.
Next
add
flour
with baking powder sifted together slowly.
Add vanilla.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for one hour.

title: baked alaska peanut s'mores
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, stir together crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons sugar and reserve about 1/4 mixture. Press remaining mixture onto bottom of flameproof 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake crust for 12 minutes or until golden and cool in pan on a rack.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken in the oil.
Place in shallow baking dish (preferably
not metal).
Saute onion in the oil.
Remove with slotted
spoon
to another pan, or drain off oil.
Add all the remaining
ingredients
and
simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken
and
place in 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting every 15 minutes.
Good served with rice.

title: heavenly cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box and bake. Add sugar to pineapple and bring to boil. Pour over cake while hot. Set aside to cool. Mix pudding as directed on box. Pour over cake. Then spread Cool Whip over cake. Sprinkle with coconut, cherries or chopped pecans, if you like.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice until it comes to a boil.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cool completely.
When cooled, add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix well and chill in 9 x 13-inch glass dish overnight.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Make a well
in
middle,
add vanilla, vinegar and oil.
Then gradually add
water.
Pour in 8-inch square pan.	Bake at 375° for 20
to
30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and sift confectioners sugar over top.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add milk slowly. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cut squash and combine with celery and onions.
Boil in 1/4 cup water until half tender.
Drain and add cream and soup to squash mixture while still hot.
Toss lightly; do not mash. Grease casserole dish and make alternate layers of squash and crackers.
Top with a few of crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and chop; set aside.
Pour oil in large mixing box. Add sugar and eggs and beat well.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Gradually add flour to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Gently fold in apples.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in batter.

title: chess pies
directions: Use any pie pastry recipe you desire and in muffin pan, mold the bottom and sides with pie pastry. Cream sugar and butter. Add the rest of the ingredients. Fill pastries almost to the top. Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes, then lower oven to 350° until done.

title: lemon buttermilk cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and beat for 3 minutes on medium speed.
(Batter will be thin.)
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a tube pan.

title: up and down biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk all at once and stir until dough follows fork around bowl.
Roll out. Spread with melted butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut and place in muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Alternate flour and milk; mix well after each addition. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in a large tube pan.

title: oriental flank steak
directions: Place steak in a large shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over steak, cover and marinate in refrigerator 8 hours, turning occasionally.

title: portia's chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter on low heat.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Cook slowly on medium heat; stir constantly until boiling.
Continue stirring; boil for 1 minute.
Take off of heat.
Add peanut butter; stir until melted.
Add oats; stir until mixed well. Teaspoon onto wax paper.
Allow 15 to 20 minutes to cool.
Store covered.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: chicken crescent squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and onion; mix well.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup of mixture into center of each rectangle.
Pull four corners to center and twist.
Seal edges and brush with 1 tablespoon butter. Bake on greased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Cook sausage and drain fat.
Butter 12 slices of white bread and place buttered side down in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Beat 6 eggs and add 1 cup milk.
Pour mixture over bread and sausage.
Sprinkle 2 cups cheese over entire dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In morning, place in oven at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: super beef-squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in salted water, about 5 minutes. Drain well.
Cook green peppers and meat until meat is no longer pink.
Stir in cooked rice.
Blend eggs, soup, sour cream and seasonings.
Stir into meat mixture.
Fold in squash mixture. Turn into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Blend all ingredients together; mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.

title: italian zucchini crescent appetizer
directions: Saute 4 cups of thinly sliced zucchini and 1 cup chopped onion in 1/2 cup of margarine for 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano.
Combine eggs and Mozzarella cheese.
Stir into the zucchini mixture.
Separate rolls into 2 long rectangles.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and 1-inch up sides to form crust. Pour zucchini mixture into crust.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes, until center is set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients. Then brown ground beef, onion and garlic and drain. Pour 1/2 cornmeal mixture in pan, then top with ground meat mixture. Add grated cheese. Pour second 1/2 cornmeal mixture on top and bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve with salsa, sour cream, chopped tomatoes and lettuce.

title: egg hors d'oeuvres
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Melt 1 stick of margarine; put half in a 13 x 9-inch pan and half in the egg mixture.
Stir together well.
Pour egg mixture into pan and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hope's biscuits
directions: Mix well; roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Bake at 425°.
Yields 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: totie field's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain well. Mix with soup, milk, tomatoes and crumbled bacon.
Pour into a 2 or 2 1/2-quart, greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place all ingredients in a 3-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until blended.
Cover and chill an hour.
Cut in squares.

title: coconut cake
directions: Follow directions for cake mix.
Poke holes in cooked cake and pour coconut milk into them.
Let cake cool.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Heat onions and celery in butter until softened (about 5 minutes).
Mix with other ingredients.
Add enough broth to moisten.

title: honey ham steak
directions: Mix oleo, dry mustard, lemon juice and honey.
Grill ham steaks direct over the coals for approximately 20 minutes.
During the last 10 minutes, baste the ham steaks with the honey glaze frequently and serve.

title: chicken in a hurry
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare couscous according to package directions.

Spread all but 2 teaspoons apricot preserves evenly over chicken pieces; arrange pieces in foil lined baking pan. Place pan in oven for about 10 minutes until chicken is heated through and well glazed with preserves.
Meanwhile, in 1-quart saucepan over high heat, bring 1/2 cup water to boil.
Add reserved apricot preserves and carrot slices and cook covered for 5 to 6 minutes until carrots are tender.
Drain carrots.
Add to couscous along with scallions and pepper.
Toss mixture well. Spoon into serving platter alongside glazed chicken.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: If using whole yams, cut in half and arrange in an oblong 2-quart baking dish.

In a saucepan, mix together cornstarch, sugars and grated orange rind. Gradually stir in orange juice, keeping smooth. Add butter. Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until boiling and thickened.
Pour over yams.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly hot. Sprinkle marshmallows over top when finished baking.
Let heat melt marshmallows or return to oven for a few minutes to brown. Makes 12 servings.

title: date-chocolate cake
directions: Mix the dates, boiling water and soda; set aside.
Cream the margarine, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, cocoa and vanilla.
Stir in date mixture.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Pour into greased oblong cake pan.
Sprinkle top of cake with 1 package of chocolate chips and 1 cup of chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cookless fruit cake
directions: Heat marshmallows and milk until marshmallows are melted.
Mix rest of ingredients together; add marshmallow mixture and mix well.
Press in loaf pan and refrigerate.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix equal parts of mayonnaise and sour cream.
(Example: 1/2 cup mayonnaise to 1/2 cup sour cream.)
Add 2 tablespoons lemon juice and garlic salt to taste.

title: garlic mayonnaise
directions: Cook garlic in 1/4 cup of the safflower oil over moderately high heat for 30 seconds.
Do not brown garlic.
Remove garlic and discard.
Let oil cool slightly.
In a food processor or blender, combine egg, lemon juice and garlic oil.
Process until smooth and well blended.
With motor running, add remaining oil, drop by drop, until mix thickens.
Then add oil in a steady stream; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add additional juice, if desired.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Grease and flour 10 x 14-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, cocoa and salt.
Add water, oil and vinegar. Top with chocolate chips and sugar. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: potato and pea croquettes
directions: After preparing the potatoes, boil and rinse in cold water. Boil the peas and drain.
Mash the potatoes and fold in all the other ingredients except the olive oil, doing the peas last.
Knead all together.
Put on a board and roll into 12 pieces.
Roll each into a patty and pan-fry in the olive oil, until golden brown on each side; about 4 minutes on each side.
Serve with Tomato Relish Sauce, found in the Soups, Salads and Sauce section.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Store in an airtight container.

title: sausage snack wraps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Cut each triangle into thirds lengthwise.
Place sausage on shortest side of each triangle.
Roll up, starting at shorter side and rolling to opposite point.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: best homemade hot chocolate
directions: Mix well and store in a dry container.
Makes 45 servings as: 1/4 cup mix to 1 cup of hot milk or water.
Drink and enjoy!

title: bonbons(chocolate peanut butter balls)
directions: Mix powdered sugar and margarine together, then add peanut butter.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Boil berries and cloves until berries are tender. Strain. Add the juice of lemons and oranges and the sugar. Mix well until sugar dissolves. Best if served hot. Makes about 16 cups.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: take it easy pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim excess fat from pork chops, leaving about 1/4 inch fat on edge.
Form oven cooking bag by closing one end with one twist-tie provided.
Place in a 1 1/2 to 2 inch deep large open roasting pan, big enough to prevent bag from extending over sides.
Place macaroni in bottom of bag.
Top with onions and green pepper.
Arrange chops on top.

title: fresh fruit pizza
directions: Mix well; bake in greased pizza pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool well.

title: roast (pork or beef)
directions: Add your seasoned roast to pot and brown. It will make water so don't add any now. Once the water cooks out and the roast browns real good on both sides, add onions and smother down (don't worry, they will brown too). Add small amounts of water (about 1 cup) at a time until tender. Cook on medium to low heat until done. Add potatoes when you see the roast is tender and cook until they are done.

title: old fashion corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Use enough shortening (or bacon drippings) to cover bottom of a small cast iron skillet. Place skillet on stove top and heat. Melted grease should cover bottom of skillet. If you do not heat the skillet, cornbread tends to stick.

title: naked apple pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add to beaten egg.
Add vanilla, chopped apples and pecans.
Mix well.
Spread mixture in a greased 9-inch pie plate and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until apples test done.
Good served warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: south of the border casserole
directions: Combine all of above except cheese and tortillas.
Butter casserole dish.
Tear tortillas in 8ths and layer with chicken mixture and cheese.
Repeat 3 times.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease bottom of 8 inch square baking pan.

title: chewy granola goodies
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil.
Butter foil; set aside. In a large saucepan, combine the marshmallows and margarine or butter.
Cook and stir mixture until the marshmallows are melted. Stir in granola with raisins, crisp rice cereal and sunflower nuts.
Press mixture into the prepared pan.
Cool.
Remove foil lining with uncut bars from pan.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24.

title: western casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper. Add garlic powder, salt and chili powder. Add tomatoes, rice, beans and olives. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake 15 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain well. In a bowl, mix meat, tomato sauce, cottage cheese, water, picante sauce and spices.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Coat chicken with taco seasoning.
Place in 8-inch square baking dish.
Cover with wax paper and cover with salsa and microwave on High 5 to 9 minutes, rotating dish once halfway through cooking.
Sprinkle with cheese and microwave on High 45 to 60 seconds or until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream if desired.
Corn and taco-coated bread sticks make wonderful side dishes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: ball park sandwich
directions: In a large skillet saute onions in margarine until clear.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and buns and simmer for 10 minutes.
Spoon mixture onto buns lined with cheese slices. Serves eight.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cut, cook and drain carrots.
Cook onions in 1/4 cup margarine until brown.
Stir in flour, salt and mustard.
Add milk and stir until smooth.
Add pepper, celery salt and cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Put carrots in casserole and pour sauce over carrots.
Mix.
Melt 1/3 cup margarine and mix with bread cubes. Put on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: souffle salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add cold water, juice, Miracle Whip, salt and pepper.
Blend.
Put in freezer to quick chill for 15 to 20 minutes until firm around edges.
Whip mixture with beaters until fluffy.
Fold in carrots, cucumber, cabbage and onion.
Refrigerate until firmly set.

title: chicken kabobs
directions: In saucepan, mix first 8 ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes. Cut chicken breasts into large chunks.
Pour marinade over chicken pieces and marinate for 3 hours.
On skewers, alternate pieces of chicken, pineapple chunks, cherry tomatoes, gree pepper, onions and mushrooms as desired.
Grill on barbecue grill until chicken is cooked through, turning to cook all sides.
Brush with remaining marinade.

title: cheeseburger pizza
directions: Grease cookie sheet. Bake biscuits 10 minutes. Then add toppings and bake 5 minutes.

title: cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop enough stems to make 1 cup.
Place in a bowl.
Stir cheese and parsley.
Boil 3 cups water and lemon juice.
Add caps and cook 1 minute.
Drain. Spread cheese mixture on mushrooms and bake 8 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together until smooth. Fold in whipped topping and pour into 9-inch graham cracker crust. Chill.
Before serving, cover top with sliced strawberries, kiwi, blueberries or fruit of your choice.

title: chicken rotel casserole
directions: Season and boil chicken.
Save broth.
Debone chicken. Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soups, tomatoes, cheeses and deboned chicken.
Add 3/4 of bag of chips and mix.
Add about 1 cup broth. You don't want it to be too soupy or too dry.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush remaining chips and pour over the top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until hot for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: frosted almond-stuffed prunes
directions: The best one that I know;

title: reuben casserole
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put sauerkraut in bottom. Layer corned beef and Swiss cheese on top of sauerkraut.
Put sliced tomatoes on top of last layer.
Dab a little butter on top of tomatoes.
Melt 1/2 cup butter; mix with crushed crackers and caraway seed.
Spread on tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: aztec chili
directions: Heat oil and add onion and garlic. Add beef; sprinkle chili powder, salt, paprika and pepper. Cook meat until brown. Drain beans (save 1/2 cup of liquid). Stir in bean liquid, paste, sugar and Tabasco sauce. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add beans and corn; simmer 15 minutes.

title: canned banana peppers
directions: Heat 1st three items to boiling and pour over peppers.
Wash peppers and cut off tops and bottoms.
Pack pint jars real tight. Pour hot vinegar mixture over peppers.
Keep caps in hot water to ensure a good sealing.

title: cinnamon cider
directions: In a large pan (Dutch oven) bring the cider to a boil.
Remove from heat and add red hot cinnamon candies.
Stir until the candies have dissolved.
Serve hot.
Serves 10 - 12.

title: thunderbolt cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Sift all dry ingredients and add alternately to cream mixture with water.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Pour in tube or favorite pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salsa copper carrots
directions: Wash, peel and cut carrots into 1/2-inch diagonal slices. Only steam the carrots 1 to 2 minutes in rolling, boiling water until they are a brighter shade of orange, still crisp and barely tender.
Drain and cool.

title: baked catfish
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; set aside.
Whisk together egg white and milk.
Dip fillets in milk mixture, then in dry mixture. Place on foil lined baking sheet that has been sprayed with Pam.
A few sesame seed can be sprinkled on the fish fillets before spraying, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Have pie crust ready.
Mix flour, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in apples.
Turn into pie crust. Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust that has slits cut in it. Seal.
Cover edge with 3-inch strips aluminum foil.
Remove foil during last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: wok vegetable casserole
directions: Heat oil in wok or large skillet.
Lightly stir-fry vegetables. Add in order.
Add kidney beans and heat through.
Season to taste with salt and oregano.
Top vegetables with cheeses.
Cover to allow cheese to melt.
Serve from wok immediately

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix together equal amounts (depending on how much dip you want to serve).
Add canned crab meat and/or canned small shrimp. Chill dip until serving time over block of cream cheese.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour, shaking off excess.
In a large nonstick pot, heat oil over medium heat.
Add beef; saute 6 minutes until brown and remove.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Saute 6 minutes. Add garlic and simmer 1 minute.
Pour off fat.
Return beef to pot and stir in tomato paste and broth.
Add enough water to just cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/4 hours and skim off foam.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Roll chicken in tortillas and place in casserole pan.
Mix soup with onion and peppers until well mixed.
Add sour cream until blended.
Place 1/2 soup mixture over tortillas, then 1/2 cheese. Bake at 400° until bubbly (about 20 minutes).
Put the rest of the soup mixture on top, then the rest of the cheese.
Bake until the cheese melts.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in large heavy iron pot.
Blend flour and stir over medium-low heat until roux is dark brown.
Add onions, celery, green peppers and garlic.
Cook until tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except rice.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: percolator punch(serves about 20)
directions: Combine pineapple juice, cranberry juice and water in a large percolator.
Into the percolator basket, place the cloves, brown sugar and smashed cinnamon sticks.
Put lid on percolator and start heating.
Allow at least 1 minute per cup for percolating time.

title: peach pickles
directions: Wash and peel peaches.
Put cloves and cinnamon loosely in clean, white cloth and tie top tightly.
Cook together spices, sugar and vinegar for 10 minutes.
Add peaches.
Cook slowly until tender, but not broken.
Remove from stove.
Let stand overnight.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight. Good with fish.
Will keep a week or more in refrigerator.

title: breakfast dish
directions: Roll one can of rolls to flatten in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 4 minutes in 350° oven.
Spread sausage over bottom, then cheese, then beaten eggs.
Flatten other can of rolls and put on top of cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: extra easy muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients, except the cinnamon sugar, in a medium mixing bowl.
Stir only until moistened completely.
Do not overbeat.
There will still be small lumps in the batter.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans.
Fill each cup 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 24 muffins.

title: chicken-almond casserole
directions: Dilute chicken soup with milk in large mixing bowl.
Add mayonnaise, chicken, rice, onion flakes, diced celery, slivered almonds and lemon juice.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and buttered corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Recipe may be doubled for larger casserole.

title: shrimp on palm pedestals
directions: Cut hearts of palm into 3/4-inch lengths and set with a cup end up on a small tray.
Mix mayonnaise, dill and lemon juice.
On top of each palm piece, place an equal amount of dill mayonnaise. Set 1 shrimp and 1 tiny dill sprig on top of each palm piece. Serve or cover and chill until the next day.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Measure all ingredients into mixer bowl.
Beat 1/2 minute at medium speed or until ingredients are mixed.
Scrape sides of bowl constantly.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes.

title: better than sex chocolate cake
directions: Beat together cake mix, eggs, oil, water, pudding mix and sour cream.
Blend well.
Add nuts, vanilla and chocolate chips and stir by hand.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
Cover with icing.

title: hot spiced fruit
directions: Pour thickened juice onto fruit in baking dish.
May be made a day
ahead.
Refrigerate.	Bake
at
325° for about 30 minutes. Can reheat.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix sour cream, spinach and mayonnaise.
Add soup mix, then rest of ingredients.
Chill a few hours.
Carve out bread, cubing carved bread when ready to serve.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in a shallow baking dish. In a small pan, melt butter; whisk in the honey, Dijon mustard, salt and curry.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste every 20 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: yellow squash pie
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender; drain.
Mix squash and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks, buttermilk and lemon extract; beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into squash mixture.
Pour into pie shells.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg. Bake for about 40 minutes at 350°, or until tests done.
