title: italian eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Beat egg. Dip in slices coated with bread crumbs, drizzling a little oil on each slice. Line cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam. Bake slices on cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven at 350° until golden brown (approximately 20 minutes). When finished baking, stack slices in shallow dish. Alternate spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese between slices. Then bake until cheese is melted. Enjoy!

title: chicken on a stick
directions: In a bowl, combine the oil, lemon juice, soy sauce, garlic honey and seasonings; mix well. Pour 1/4 cup marinade into a large resealable plastic bag; add the chicken. Seal bag and turn to coat; refrigerate for at least 3 to 4 hours.
Cover and refrigerate remaining marinade.

title: tomato soup casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon.
Cook noodles.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, put in layers.
First noodles, then hamburger mixture, then corn. Repeat layers.
Cover with tomato soup mixed with some water or milk and sprinkle with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken italian style
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in olive oil until soft; remove from pan.
Flour chicken lightly and brown on both sides in same pan. Add remaining ingredients to pan and cook until chicken is tender. Serve over vermicelli.

title: squash dressing
directions: Boil the squash and onion in water until tender.
Drain; then add the soup, eggs and corn bread.
Last, blend in the melted butter.
Pour into a glass pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 400° until firm.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Chop broccoli and chicken and mix together.
Heat soups and Cheez Whiz.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.

title: aunt hattie's ginger cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, molasses, spices and baking soda.
Add flour.
Chill dough.
Roll dough in balls.
Dip in sugar and place 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine berries, sugar, tapioca, water and butter and let stand while making crust.
Sift flour, 2 teaspoons sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk all at once.
Roll out, cut into 8 (2 1/2-inch) rounds and sprinkle each with sugar.
Add lemon extract to berries and pour into baking dish.
Place rounds over berries and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma edie's overnight noodle pudding
directions: Turn all but egg whites and noodles into blender.
Whirl until smooth, then drain noodles and fold into mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter and turn into buttered glass baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine kraut, onion and peppers.
Mix vinegar, oil, sugar and water.
Pour over kraut.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Mix dry ingredients in bowl; beat eggs.
Add with rest of ingredients; mix well into batter.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Use toothpick test.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream
oleo;
add
sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Sift dry
ingredients;
add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, bananas and nuts.
Bake in 2 large loaf pans at 350°.

title: dukes corn bread pudding
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish (8 x 12-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts or whole chicken (whatever you need) in salt water until it can be pulled away from the bones.
(Save 2 cups of broth from chicken.)
In saucepan, melt butter; add onion and celery and saute in bottom of baking dish.
Put in chicken (without bones) and sprinkle with sage.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Add butter, onion and celery.
Top with dressing mix.
Pour broth over dressing mix to moisten dressing mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of meat mix, chips and cheese in a 2-quart dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat with onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add all canned vegetables.
Add dry Hidden Valley mix and taco mix. Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over Fritos and top with grated cheese.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, apples and walnuts.
Beat together the eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix all together and pour into greased and floured pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool and frost with lemon-butter frosting or garnish with Cool Whip.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix eggs, bananas, Crisco and sugar in a blender.
Pour into a bowl and add dry ingredients.
Mix well.

title: cake
directions: Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Press out onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: pinwheel biscuits with eggs and broccoli
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a square baking dish.
Heat butter in saucepan.
Stir in 2 tablespoons Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth.
Stir in 4 cups milk slowly.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickens.
Add cheese, eggs and broccoli.
Spread in baking dish.

title: vanilla wafers cake
directions: Cream together sugar, milk, butter, coconut, pecans, vanilla, eggs and vanilla wafers. Mix well. Line bottom of pan with Reynolds Wrap. Grease pan with butter, then sprinkle with flour in pan lightly. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. When cake is done, leave in pan for 4 to 5 minutes before taking out.

title: brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10 to 11-inch pizza pan. Prepare brownie mix according to directions.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edge of pan. Remove from oven and sprinkle with peanut butter cups and marshmallows.
Return to oven and bake 5 minutes or until marshmallows begin to puff.
Remove from oven and add M&M's. Makes 16 slices.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Melt butter in large heavy saucepan.
Add onions, celery and bell peppers.
Cook 10 minutes until clear.
Add flour; blend in well.
Cover and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add parsley and crawfish tails.
Cover and cook 20 minutes, stirring often.
Add creams, wine, cheese, jalapenos and garlic.
Mix well. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook covered on low heat 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: lime cucumber pickles
directions: In a 5 gallon stone churn or larger, put 3 gallons water and 3 cups lime (hydrated).
Stir.
Slice cucumbers 1/4-inch thick.
Put in the lime water.
Let set 24 hours and wash through 3 waters and cover with water and let stand overnight.

title: crock-pot spinach casserole
directions: Mix all this together.
Put in greased crock-pot.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours on high or 3 to 4 hours on low.

title: tiger butter(microwave)
directions: Melt white chocolate in microwave.
Stir every 2 minutes until melted.
Beat in peanut butter.
Pour onto cookie sheet (wax papered).
Melt chips, drizzle over mixture and swirl with knife. Chill and cut.

title: butterscotch rice krispie candy
directions: Line 9 x 12-inch pan with wax paper.
Melt in microwave: morsels and peanut butter about 4 minutes; check and stir about every minute until melted.
In large bowl, mix mixture and Rice Krispies.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate until hard.
Cut into squares.

title: fruited cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream and stir until melted.
Add cherries, pineapple and pecans.
Place in 2-quart mold and refrigerate. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: poppy seed water crackers
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 400°. Lightly grease large cookie sheet.
Into medium bowl, measure flour, baking powder and salt with fork; stir in olive or salad oil and 1/3 cup water until well blended.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples; put in pie crust.
Pour flour mixture (first 4 ingredients) over apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit and nut bread pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine bread and sugar; set aside.
In another bowl, beat eggs, milk, cinnamon, salt and vanilla until foamy. Pour over bread and sugar; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Stir in all remaining ingredients, except cream.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Melt margarine, all but 1 tablespoon, in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Toss spaghetti in pan.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon of margarine. Pour pizza sauce over spaghetti and mix.
Top with half of Swiss cheese, half of pepperoni and half of Mozzarella.
Add mushrooms, onion and spices.
Repeat cheese and meat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cherry pie supreme
directions: Spread half of cherry pie filling in the pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 350°.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over hot pie filling.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato and marshmallow casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole.
Place marshmallows on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, reserving 1 cup of juice.
Combine with pudding mix.
Cook until clear; cool.
Add fruit.
While preparing, I rinse banana chunks with lemon juice to keep them from turning dark.

title: pastry for 1 crust 8 or 9-inch pie
directions: Combine Crisco, flour and salt, mixing with a fork or pastry blender until the mixture forms coarse crumbs, making sure that the shortening is distributed evenly.
Add the water, one tablespoon at a time, tossing quickly with a fork.
When mixture is still crumbly but moist enough to hold together with slight pressure, stop tossing.
Flatten into a disk and roll out to desired size on lightly floured board or pastry sheet.
Transfer rolled pastry dough to pie pan.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and cream cheese until well blended. Add eggs (one at a time) until mixed.
Add vanilla.
Slowly add flour; mix.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan; bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours, or until golden brown.
Serve plain, or frost lightly with butter frosting.

title: light strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 9X13 inch baking dish.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine apples, 1 1/2 cups water and lemon juice.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes and stir in vanilla.
In a medium bowl, stir together 1 cup flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender until crumbly.
Stir in 1/2 cup water until just combined.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet and drain off excess grease.
Microwave chopped onions until tender, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Add catsup to browned ground beef first, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: mock chicken legs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine seasoning salt and flour. Alternate pork and veal on wooden skewer.
Dredge in seasoned flour.
Dip in egg and milk and pepper, and coat with cracker crumbs.
Fry in oil with half the onions.
Put in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add 1/4-inch water; cover with 1/2 diced onions.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour.
Uncover foil and bake 10 minutes more.

title: cherry nut jello
directions: Heat juice of fruit and dissolve Jello, add cold Cokes.
When slightly jelled, add cherries, pineapple and pecans. Stir and chill.

title: chili cheese squares
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add flour, salt and baking powder; blend together.
Pour in chilies and cheeses.
Pour melted butter from 9 x 13-inch pan (leaving pan coated), into egg mixture.
Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 30 minutes more. Do not overcook.

title: cranberry juice cocktail
directions: Combine cranberries and water in saucepan.
Boil gently until skins pop open.
Strain through cheesecloth.
Return to heat.
Add sugar and boil.
Chill.

title: baked cranberry-orange sauce
directions: Wash cranberries and drain.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Add cranberries, stirring well.
Place cranberry mixture in a 9-inch square pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add marmalade, walnuts and lemon juice; stir well and cool.
To store, refrigerate in a tightly covered container. Serve hot or cold.
Yields 5 cups.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger meat and chopped onion. Drain well. Add tomato sauce, paste and water.
Add oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes. Cook spaghetti according to directions on package. Serve sauce on top or mix all together. May sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top, if desired.

title: savory rump roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides; place in microwave pressure cooker. Combine all remaining ingredients, except cornstarch, and pour over meat.
Cover and add red weight.
Microwave on High for 35 minutes. Allow pressure indicating stem to drop, then remove roast.
Skim fat.
Dissolve cornstarch in small amount of liquid (wine or water), then add to juices in cooker.
Cook, uncovered, for 2 to 3 minutes to thicken.
To serve, slice roast and pour sauce over.

title: christmas stollen
directions: Combine milk, 1 cup melted butter and 1/2 cup water in a small saucepan.
Place over low heat just until lukewarm.
Combine flour, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and yeast in a large mixing bowl; stir in warm milk mixture and eggs, mixing well.
Add lemon and orange rind, raisins, fruit and nuts; mix well.
Cover dough and refrigerate overnight.

title: hamburg sausage
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Next morning take out and knead 5 minutes and return to refrigerator. Repeat next 2 days.
On 4th day, shape into rolls, not over 2 inches across.
Place on rack with pan underneath to catch drippings.
Bake at 200° in oven for 5 hours, turning them at 2 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly, but well.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in bowl.
Add flour mixture to first mixture and blend.
Bakes in 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or bake in a Bundt pan sprayed with Pam in microwave for 14 to 16 minutes on high.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick butter on top of double boiler; set aside.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Cream sugar and remaining butter until thoroughly blended.
Alternately add eggs, flour and buttermilk.
Stir into melted candy bars and butter.
Add pecans. Pour into tube pan and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix as you would any cake.
Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours. This cake is good.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and then pour into a flat container which has the bottom covered with graham cracker crust (see directions for crust on the cracker box).
Save some of the crumbs to sprinkle over top of filling.
Then add broken nut meats and some of the cherries as a top garnish.
Place in freezer for several hours. Remove half hour before serving.

title: soup in a bun
directions: Saute vegetables in butter. Add broth; simmer 20 minutes.
Add potato soup and cheese.
Just before serving in bun, add sour cream.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat 4 minutes on medium. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: southern stew
directions: Put tomatoes, corn and greens in large pot and simmer.
Add beans and onions, if desired.
Stew 10 minutes.

title: chinese sesame cookies(heung yun beng)
directions: In an electric mixer, mix all of the ingredients except the flour and sesame seed together.
Add the flour.
Be sure not to overmix at this point, you only want to mix it until it holds together. Roll dough into walnut size balls and then roll in the sesame seed.
Place on a cookie sheet about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until cookies have irregular cracks on the surface.

title: eggnog
directions: Combine custard mix and sugar.
Blend in 1 cup milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mix comes to boil.
Stir in remaining 2 cups milk.

title: pizza dish
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
Add onion, pizza sauce, mushrooms and spices.
Layer in a casserole dish (2-quart).
Do 2 layers.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown crumbled sausage and drain off fat.
Return to pan and add cheeses; warm thoroughly.
It's ready to serve.

title: shrimp francese
directions: Peel, devein and butterfly shrimp, leaving tail attached. Dredge shrimp in flour.
Shake off excess and dip in beaten eggs. Heat butter in large skillet.
(Iron skillet may darken shrimp.) Saute shrimp until golden on both sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken and asian noodle salad
directions: Thoroughly cook chicken breasts and thinly slice; set aside. Cook Chinese noodles according to package instructions. In a small non-reactive bowl, whisk together rice wine vinegar, miso and sesame oil until well combined.
Set aside.
In a medium size bowl, combine chicken, noodles, tomatoes, green beans, arugula or other salad greens and cilantro.
Drizzle miso vinaigrette over salad and toss until evenly coated.
Taste and adjust seasoning. If using papayas, place half a papaya on each of 4 plates.
Divide salad evenly among papaya halves or serve in cool Asian style bowls if you prefer.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix chicken, seasonings and soup together.
Put spaghetti in baking dish and add mixture.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake(child snack recipe)
directions: Mix strawberries with Equal to desired sweetness.
Top angel food cake with strawberries.
Add 1/2 tablespoon whipped topping.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Let milk and sugar come to a boil.
Add cornstarch and 1/2 ground coconut.
After it has boiled, add egg whites, well beaten. Put in 3 baked crusts.
Top with remaining ground coconut.

title: "all in one" meal
directions: In a greased casserole dump all ingredients; stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: creme dip for strawberries
directions: Mix until creamy the sour cream and cream cheese. Add confectioners sugar and mix good.

title: bean and cheese burritos
directions: To soften tortillas, stack and wrap in foil.
Heat in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile in a medium saucepan, cook the onion in water until tender.
Do not drain.

Stir in the refried beans and green chilies; cook and stir until heated through. Spoon about 1/3 cup of the bean mixture onto each tortilla. Sprinkle about 3 tablespoons of the Monterey Jack cheese on top of the bean mixture; roll up tortilla.
Place on a foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake loosely covered in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: baked doughnuts or cinnamon rolls
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, stir sugar, salt, nutmeg, shortening and milk until shortening is melted.
Cool.
Add eggs and yeast dissolved in water.
Add flour and beat.
Add flour as needed. Let rise to double.
Knead and roll to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut and place on greased cookie sheets and let rise again.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.
Finish as desired.

title: lola's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and heat until margarine and sugar melt.
I make this ahead of time, refrigerate and use as needed. Good with chicken or pork.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time.
Combine baking powder, flour and salt and add to mix alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mangos
directions: For presentation, put chips between the two halves of the Hero.
Put mangos on a lettuce leaf.
The Hero is so filling no dessert is needed.

title: easy holiday squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and vanilla; beat well.
Spread evenly into a greased jelly roll pan. Score the top lightly with a knife to make squares.
Place 1 tablespoon pie filling in center of each square.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: diabetic peanut butter balls
directions: Use a vegetable spray to lightly grease cookie sheet.
Cream peanut butter in a small bowl.
Add cake mix and water.
Beat at low speed until mixture is thoroughly blended.
Mixture will be large, moist crumbs.
Form into 30 balls.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add alternately to the mixture the hot milk, flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased lined pan for 35 to 40 minutes until center springs back.

title: christmas bread
directions: Proof yeast in warm water for 5 minutes. Add biscuit mix, 1 tablespoon sugar and egg. Stir well. Knead dough on floured surface until smooth. Place in buttered bowl. Turn to grease top and chill 8 hours. Punch dough down and turn into greased 14 x 9-inch baking sheet. Roll dough out to fit sheet. Combine cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice. Beat together until smooth. Spread mixture 2 inches wide down the length of the dough. Make 3-inch cuts in dough at 1-inch intervals along the edges. Fold and overlap strips diagonally to make a braid. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and spoon preserves down the center. Return to oven for 5 minutes to melt. Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: orange chicken wings
directions: Stir eggs with fork; add orange juice.
Dip chicken wings into mixture and roll in flour.

title: strawberries cup dessert
directions: Whip evaporated milk until thick (before using evaporated milk be sure it is real cold).
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar to egg whites, beating until stiff.
Add lemon juice, then strawberries.
Beat at high speed with mixer until thick. Fold in evaporated milk.
Put in glass cups and freeze.
Ready to eat any time.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and drain spinach; fry bacon and drain.
Crumble the bacon in small pieces and put it in the spinach.
Slice eggs and add to the spinach.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and let stand until partially thickened.
Whip gelatin until light and fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream, angel food cake pieces and sliced strawberries.
Chill until firm.

title: tuna salad pie(or crab meat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine tuna, celery, salt, onion, eggs, green pepper, mayonnaise, lemon juice and all but 2 tablespoons of bread crumbs.
Mix lightly.
Turn into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with the reserved bread crumbs and cheese.
Place on solid cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes or until firm and brown.

title: good snack
directions: Mix together all but crackers.
Pour over crackers.
Stir to coat.
Place in
a
200° oven 15 to 20 minutes. Shake every few minutes.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Roast pecans in butter 15 minutes in a 300° oven.
Melt the cream cheese in a bowl in microwave on Medium (50%) for 3 to 5 minutes.
Mix in sugar with beater.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan. Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: shredded-beef sandwiches
directions: Trim fat from roast.
Cut roast, as necessary, to fit into a 3 or 4-quart electric crock-pot.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the meat.
Cover and cook on low heat setting for 11 to 12 hours or until meat is very tender.
Remove meat and use two forks to shred meat; discard bay leaves, fat and bones.
Serve on buns (French rolls are great with this).
Strain meat juices; skim off fat juices.
Serve juices with sandwiches for dipping.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook to firm ball stage. Beat well and pour on cake.
This is a simple, easy caramel icing. No more burnt sugar to make caramel.

title: spring fling fruit tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour and brown sugar in bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Knead mixture until well blended.
Press onto 1/2-inch up sides of 10-inch tart pan with removable bottom.
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: potato-spinach casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients, except the cheese. Spoon mixture into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer until lightly browned.

title: missionary date balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in pan.
Cook until thick, about 8 minutes, stirring over low heat.
Cool slightly.
Place nuts and rice cereal in a large bowl.
Add date mixture and mix well.
With buttered hands, form into tiny balls.
Roll in coconut, finely chopped nuts or granulated sugar.
Yield: 2 to 3 dozen.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt together.
Add to the creamed mixture. Combine the molasses and water; add to the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
This is good served with raisin sauce or lemon sauce.

title: old-fashion corn pudding
directions: Cut corn off the cob, scraping ears.
Add sugar, flour, salt and pepper.
Blend in beaten eggs, butter and milk.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: mother's caramel pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, thick cream and butter in saucepan and boil until thick.
Mix well milk, flour and eggs and pour into first mixture, stirring constantly.
Makes 2 pies.

title: quick supper rice 'n tuna
directions: Mix cream of celery soup, tuna together and heat.
Pour over cooked rice and serve.
Serve with salad and hot bread.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except chili powder.
Sprinkle chili powder on balls.
Makes 2 large balls.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Combine 1st 5 dry ingredients in mixing bowl. In separate bowl combine carrots, apples, raisins and walnuts.
Stir in eggs, oil, vanilla and coconut.
Add this mixture to dry ingredients until thoroughly moistened.
Pour into muffin tin sprayed with no stick spray.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 25 minutes.

title: mango cake
directions: Cream
margarine and sugar.
Add eggs
and
beat
well. Mix soda and mangos; add to creamed
mixture.
Sift
together all other ingredients and add to mixture.
Grease
and
flour pan. Use either tube pan, 2 loaf pans or Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: butter pecan pound cake
directions: Grease Bundt or tube pan and dust with powdered sugar on the bottom of pan. Sprinkle chopped nuts also in the bottom of the pan. Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and water. Mix for 2 minutes or until smooth. Stir icing into cake batter and mix well. Pour batter into pan on top of pecans and powdered sugar. Bake at 325° for about 55 minutes or until done. Let cool for at least 20 minutes before turning onto cake plate.

title: olive cheese puffs
directions: Beat cheese and butter together until creamy, then gradually add flour.
Add pepper and mix well.
Take about 1 teaspoonful of dough and mold around each olive.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: vegetable chicken
directions: Layer peppers, onions, tomatoes and chicken on bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Season chicken as you like.
Repeat chicken, peppers, onions and tomatoes.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 1 hour.
Great on the grill.

title: yogurt-oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix yogurt with oatmeal; let stand 1 hour. Cream margarine with sugar. Beat in egg and oatmeal mixture. Combine dry ingredients; add to oatmeal mixture.
Stir in raisins. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: company casserole
directions: Mix rice with melted butter or margarine in crock pot.
Add all remaining ingredients except sliverd almonds and 2 Tbsp. green onions.
Stir well.
Sprinkle reserved almonds and green onions over top.
Cover and cook on low heat 7-9 hours or on high for 3-4 hours.

title: georgia peach bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add peach puree and dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Add vanilla and chopped pecans; stir until blended.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, approximately 5 x 9-inches in size, that have been well-greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes to 1 hour. Let bread cool a few minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: brownie mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight canister.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together.
Combine the egg, milk and oil in a separate bowl.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and add the wet ingredients all at once.
Stir quickly, just until moistened.
Gently stir in the blueberries.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together ingredients in a large bowl.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Make into small balls.
Put sausage balls on glass baking dish.
Spray Pam on dish.
Bake for 25 minutes, turning over to brown both sides.
Drain on paper towels and serve warm.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat lightly just until combined (don't overbeat or brownies will rise too high).
Stir in flour and "optional" ingredients.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.
Cut in bars.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix and make into balls about the size of a nickel.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: daddy's mary mix
directions: Put all ingredients in a gallon jug.
Shake well.
Fill glasses with
ice
(add
vodka, if desired). Add celery stalk, lemon, salt and pepper.
Serve.

title: sweet dinner muffins
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add egg and beat well. Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Put in muffin pans and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: liver stir-fried with onions
directions: On cutting board, cut liver into 1/4-inch strips.
On waxed paper, coat liver with flour.
In 12-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook liver about 3 minutes or until brown, stirring frequently.
Add onions and soy sauce. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until onions are tender-crisp and liver is tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jalapeno relish
directions: Mix together all ingredients and cook, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(The amount of jalapenos may be varied to taste.)
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Pour into hot jars and water bath 35 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: easy eclair dessert
directions: Prepare pudding mix using package directions, reducing milk to 3 cups.
Fold in whipped topping. Layer graham crackers and pudding mixture alternately in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, ending with graham crackers.
Spread frosting over crackers.
Chill, covered, for 8 hours or longer.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer.
Top with meringue or marshmallows (optional).

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
In saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with margarine.
In mixer bowl, beat chocolate mixture with sweetened condensed milk, biscuit mix, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into prepared pastry shell. Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Serve warm or at room temperature with ice cream, if desired.

title: chocolate marshmallow frosting
directions: Melt chocolate in milk in top of double boiler over simmering water; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat and beat in sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Cool slightly; fold in marshmallows.
Frost cookies.
Yields frosting for 4 dozen cookies.

title: breakfast pancakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together.
Beat egg; add milk.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Mix.
Add melted butter. When griddle has reached correct temperature, pour the pancakes. When full of bubbles, turn only once.

title: hot-spiced fruit punch
directions: Place cloves and cinnamon in center of a small piece of cheesecloth; tie securely.
Place spice bag and remaining ingredients in a large saucepan; stir to blend well.
Cook, over medium heat, 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Serve hot. Makes 10 cups.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Beat cream cheese in large mixer bowl. Add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add lemon peel and vanilla.
Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Bake until firm, about 1 hour.
Cool to room temperature. Refrigerate at least 3 hours, but no longer than 10 days.
Top with Strawberry Glaze.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Line a baking dish with 1 cup rice.
Arrange chicken pieces on rice.
Sprinkle 1/2 package of onion soup on chicken. Dissolve beef bouillon in water and pour over chicken pieces.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Cover and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in water for 3 minutes.
Add 1 cup flour, cake mix, eggs, oil and salt.
Using mixer, beat until bubbles appear. Add remaining flour slowly.
Add more flour if necessary to work dough.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and roll out 1/4-inch thick. Spread with soft butter and sprinkle with a mixture of 1 cup brown sugar and 4 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll like jelly roll and cut in 1-inch pieces.
Place on greased pan and let rise until double in size.
Makes approximately 40 buns.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: murrel's fruit balls
directions: Beat together eggs, molasses and oil. Add juice, then rest of the ingredients. Mix with hands. Roll into balls. Put on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 50 large balls.

title: elephant stew
directions: Blessed is she whose daily tasks are a labor of love; for her willing hands and happy heart translate duty into privilege and her labor becomes a service to God and to all mankind.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients, then fold in cool whip. Chill before serving.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and add to wet ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot oil and brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: ice cream sandwich cake
directions: Lay one layer of ice cream sandwiches in the bottom of a casserole dish. Spread one layer of Cool Whip on top. Lay second layer of ice cream sandwiches on next. Spread second layer of Cool Whip. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of top layer of Cool Whip. Place in freezer until ready to eat.

title: chicken paella
directions: Fry chicken in olive oil until browned.
If using thighs, remove all bones and chop into bite size pieces.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add rice, water, Bijol, bouillon and black pepper.
Bring to boil.
Cover and lower heat to simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Add chicken and drained peas.
Simmer 5 minutes more or until moisture is absorbed!

title: bread pudding(kids love this)
directions: Beat eggs in large Pyrex bowl.
Add broken bread, vanilla, sugar, raisins and milk.
Mix slightly.
Then sprinkle nutmeg and cinnamon over top.
Add butter to top also.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (you need to set the dish in a pie pan of warm water).

title: hamburger and baked beans
directions: Saute
bacon and onion.
Add hamburger and brown; drain grease.
Add
remaining ingredients, mix and pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 or 9.

title: bean-n-bacon soup
directions: Mix cooked beans, vegetables and ham together.
To each quart add 1 teaspoon salt.
Makes about 16 quarts.
Pressure cook at 10 pounds pressure for 1 hour.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in salted water; drain.
Add celery soup and Ritz crackers.
Make a sauce from melted butter.
Add flour and salt; stir well.
Add cheese and blend until cheese is melted. Combine all and sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Ingredients will be in layers.
First put spaghetti sauce on bottom of pan then lay noodles gently in pan.
Pour more sauce on top of noodles.
Then add hamburger layer.
Sprinkle mushrooms and cheese.
Keep on repeating until all is used up.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian teriyaki
directions: Cube steak or cut in strips.
Stir into marinade and refrigerate overnight or at room temperature for 2 hours.
Put onto skewers with water chestnuts.
Cook on grill for 12 minutes. Baste with sauce.

title: cameo cake
directions: Combine butter and water in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add white chocolate, stirring until chocolate melts.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla; set aside.
Combine flour and pecans, stirring to coat.
Set aside.
Combine remaining 3 cups flour, sugar and soda in a large bowl; gradually stir in white chocolate mixture.
Fold in pecan mixture (batter will be thin).
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cool in pans or on wire racks for 10 minutes; remove from pans and let cool.
Spread White Chocolate-Cream Cheese Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Yields one 3 layer cake.

title: melon balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine the fruits. In a separate bowl, combine the main ingredients. Pour dressing over the fruit. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: lasagna
directions: Grease two 13 x 11 glass baking dishes.
Prepare lasagna in oiled boiling salted water.
Brown meats one at a time.
Combine together for meat layer.
Mix eggs with Romano in small bowl.
Add Ricotta to make cheese mix.

title: hot tang tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon.
To make your cup of hot tea, combine 3 heaping teaspoons of tea mixture to cup of hot water.

title: cabbage skillet
directions: Mix and saute in skillet until all ingredients are tender-crisp.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Add margarine, eggs and milk.
Then add pecans and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. About half way through cooking, place a piece of aluminum foil over pie to prevent crust from getting too brown.
Make sure pie is dry to touch before removing from oven.
Makes 1 deep-dish pie.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Mix well and make a soft dough.
Roll like pie crust, brush and add sugar, cinnamon and margarine.
Brush.
Spread over pie crust and then fold over and cut in strips.
After cut in strips, make 1 knot.
Bake at 350°.

title: wild chinese rice
directions: Mix contents of box, soup and water in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add Chinese vegetables.
Arrange pork chops on top; sprinkle with pepper.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°. Serve with Chinese noodles and soy sauce.

title: breakfast eggs
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lay bread close together.
Place sausage on top, then Cheddar and Swiss cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk, half and half, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and salt.
Pour over bread and sausage.
Refrigerate overnight or 6 to 8 hours. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture with fruit and nuts.
Place in greased square pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream cream cheese, margarine and vanilla together.
Add sifted sugar until spreading consistency.
Use on red velvet, carrot cake, Italian cream or any plain pound cake for delicious flavor.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Divide batter into 2 loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, corn syrup, butter and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring over medium heat to 236°.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add flavoring.
Beat until mixture starts to lose its gloss (about 8 minutes).
Stir in cherries and walnuts and quickly pour into a greased shallow pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheesy ham stuffed pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a large cookie sheet.
Mix ham, half of the soup and 2 tablespoons of the onions.
Stir baking mix, margarine, water and mustard until soft dough forms. Turn onto surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 5 times.
Roll into 13-inch circle; place on cookie sheet.
Spread ham mixture over crust to within 2-inches of edge.
Fold edge over mixture, leaving about 4-inch opening in center. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 25 to 27 minutes or until crust is light golden brown and cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with remaining onions.
Heat remaining soup. Serve with pie.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Drain and place in a Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients and enough water to cover by 2 inches.
Cook slowly for 2 hours; stir occasionally.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
Mash a few beans to thicken gravy.
Serve with rice, salsa and cornbread.
Freezes well, also.

title: red cabbage and apples
directions: In a large bowl, combine yogurt, honey and vinegar. Stir until smooth.
Add apples, cabbage and raisins and mix well. Cover and chill at least 15 minutes.
Toss again before serving. Drain liquid.
Use slotted spoon to serve.
Serves 4.

title: hunt's tomato sauce casserole
directions: While water is boiling for macaroni, brown hamburger and celery in large frypan.
When the meat is browned, add tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Let this simmer while macaroni boils.
Drain macaroni and put back into the large pot it was boiled in, then add sauce mixture to it.
Mix well, then put in Pyrex casserole and cover with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts. When reheating leftovers, put aluminum foil over it.
Serve with the rest of celery stalks as a salad.

title: sweet dill crispy pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers
with boiling water.
Stand for 24 hours.
Drain; repeat this process for 4 days.
On the 5th day, drain and slice in 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine sugar, spices, salt and vinegar.
Bring to boil and pour over pickles.
Let stand 2 days.
On the 3rd day, bring to a boil and seal in hot jars.
Do not overcook.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine milk, sugar and eggs in large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, about 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture thickens and coats a metal spoon (160°).
Remove from heat.
Stir in cream and vanilla; chill.
Freeze in ice cream maker according to manufacturer's directions.
After freezing, transfer ice cream to plastic freezer container.
Place in freezer to ripen at least 3 hours before serving.

title: taco soup
directions: Dump in crock-pot and leave the house!

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: In bottom of large bowl, place 3 cups of lettuce.
Sprinkle with a little sugar, salt, and pepper.
Layer eggs on top of lettuce, standing some on end if desired.
Sprinkle generously with salt.
Next layer in order: peas, remaining lettuce, bacon and cheese.
Spread mayonnaise or salad dressing over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight. Garnish with sliced green onions and paprika.
Toss before serving.
Serves 12-15.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Heat juices from cherries and pineapple.
Dissolve Jell-O in juices, then add pineapple, cherries (cut in half), nuts and Coke. Mix up and chill overnight.
Great with turkey.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add flavoring and eggs (mix).
Add milk and bananas.
Add all dry ingredients into bowl.
Mix well. Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan and let stand 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then add pineapple, Cool Whip and 1/2 cup pecans, one at a time.
Pour in serving dish and top with remaining pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: dang good pie(makes 1 pie)
directions: Melt oleo and mix with remaining ingredients (except pie shell).
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set and brown.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Mix all together.
Cook in pot on stove top for 1 1/2 hours or you can cook in crock-pot on high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Put cabbage and onions in layers, ending with onions.
Combine all other ingredients except oil in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat and add oil.
Pour over cabbage and onions. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: "three king's cake"
directions: Boil together for 3 minutes brown sugar, water, oil, raisins, dates, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Cool in bowl.
Then add baking soda mixed with boiled water.
Blend in flour and baking powder.
Add chopped nuts (optional).
Pour into a greased round tube pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for about 50 minutes. Let cool for about 30 minutes and turn over onto flat plate.

title: sauce for shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and use as a dip for shrimp.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix the above together and beat.
Pour a little juice from a can of pineapple (not too much because it will be soupy).
Pour on graham crust.
Cover pan with bananas (usually takes 4 or 5) until pan is covered good.
Add drained pineapple, spread with Cool Whip and garnish top with nuts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: sadie's scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease a large casserole dish with butter and then rub with garlic clove. Place half of potatoes in dish.
Salt and pepper them to taste.
Sprinkle with half of shredded cheese.
Layer remaining potatoes and cheese.
Pour heavy cream over.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Remove foil and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: egg breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in well buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake the next day for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: kid's cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large mixer bowl, mix shortening, 1 3/4 cups sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat, scraping bowl occasionally.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put in seasoning, celery and onions when boiling chicken.
Put chicken in casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and chicken soup.
Pour over 36 hand crushed Ritz crackers.
Mix in 2 teaspoons poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Combine other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Good with a barbecue.

title: cheesy macaroni bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Drain fat and mix all other ingredients except cheese.
Put in casserole dish and cover with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of blender. Process until smooth. Store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: fried squash(easy, quick, delicious)
directions: Combine flour and cornmeal.
Salt and pepper squash slices and dredge in flour/cornmeal mix.
Heat oil in skillet.
Fry squash in hot oil until just golden brown (4 or 5 minutes on each side).
Cook on medium-high heat.

title: oven omelet(for breakfast or dinner)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt together.
Pour into pan. Sprinkle with green onions.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness. Cut into squares (12 to 15).
Serves 6.

title: heart cookies
directions: Beat margarine, shortening and peanut butter well.
Add egg and beat well.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla and milk to mixture.
Chill 2 hours or more.
Roll dough on lightly floured board to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out cookies with heart-shaped cookie cutters.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes (until lightly brown).
Move cookies to cooling rack. Spread 1 tsp. jam on a cookie and cover with another cookie for a peanut butter and jelly effect.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over a medium heat.
Add beef, onion and green pepper, cooking until there's no more pink to the meat; drain liquid.
Stir in remaining ingredients; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, salt and water in top of double boiler. Boil to a thick syrup.
Mix 1/4 cup milk and cornstarch to thick paste.
Add 1 3/4 cups milk, then stir into hot syrup.
Cook over hot water until thick and smooth, then cook 15 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Stir small amount of mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Return to boiler and cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: herb sticks
directions: Split buns in quarters lengthwise.
Set out overnight so they are easier to spread.
Blend butter and herbs; spread on cut surfaces of buns.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Arrange buns on cookie sheet; bake for 45 to 60 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 32 sticks.
Store in covered container.
Can be done in microwave.

title: crab fondue
directions: Combine all except crab.
Heat over low heat or microwave to melt cheese.
Add drained washed crabmeat.
Serve warm with freshly cut chunks of sourdough bread or rolls.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.

title: igloos
directions: Heat butter and mix with sugar.
Add vanilla, pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper.
Stack buttercup cookies 3 high and pour heated ingredients between each cookie.
Makes 16 in all.
Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: baked stuffed chicken breast
directions: Mix up 2 cups Bell's stuffing according to package directions. Add carrot, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Place chicken breasts rib side up on foil covered cookie tin.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Place a large scoop of stuffing in each rib cage half, topping with a pat of butter.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until done.

title: skillet macaroni and cheese
directions: In skillet, melt butter; add onion and saute until tender. Stir in flour, salt and oregano.
Add macaroni and milk.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted (do not boil).

title: angel food almond balls
directions: Cut a loaf angel food cake into squares about 1 1/2-inches across.
Trim off corners so that cake will look slightly round. Cream butter; add confectioners sugar gradually.
Beat well. Flavor with vanilla or almond extract or any flavoring you prefer. Add double cream.
Completely cover the cake rounds with butter and sugar mixture; roll in ground toasted almonds.
Best to serve soon after making.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream oleo, oil, sugars and eggs, add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together, mix in.
Chill at least one hour.
Pinch small balls, place on greased cookie sheet, flatten with fork or bottom of glass dipped in flour (or sugar).
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes until edges begin to brown.
Dough keeps indefinitely in refrigerator to cook as desired.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Mix cereal, buttermilk, oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Stir into cereal mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours before using.
When ready, fill paper lined muffin tins 2/3 full.
(Batter will keep for 6 weeks, covered, in refrigerator.)
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: frosty lime pie
directions: Heat applesauce
to boiling.
Add lime gelatin and stir until dissolved.	Mix
in
sugar.
Cool
until
almost
stiff. Whip 1 cup
very
cold evaporated milk with lime juice.
Pour into gelatin mixture, beating slowly.
Place in baked shell or graham cracker crust.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas in bowl; add oil and mix well.
Add egg and mix. Add sugar and mix.
Measure flour; add salt and soda.
Mix together and add banana mixture.
Stir well.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Grease and flour 12 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: wedding cake icing
directions: Cream shortening and vanilla together until smooth. Then add sifted sugar a little at a time with a little water until creamy.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Brown meat and drain. Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder until hot. Layer in 2-quart casserole half each of meat mixture, chips and cheese. Repeat layers. Bake 20 to 30 minutes until thoroughly heated. Top with diced tomato, shredded lettuce and sour cream, if desired.

title: crazy crunch-cheese spread
directions: Blend together softened cream
cheese
and Velveeta cheese. Add garlic salt, mixing well.
Stir in nuts.
Serve with a variety of snack crackers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop onions and broccoli.
Add all ingredients and stir.

title: great grits casserole
directions: Cook grits as directed on package.
Add butter and pepper to hot grits.
Stir to mix.
Add 1 cup cheese.
Add some hot grits to eggs.
Combine eggs and grits.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Top with remaining 1 cup cheese and parsley.
Bake additional 10 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine.
Add onion and mushrooms; saute until onion is tender, about 3 minutes.
Add soup and cheeses; cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Thaw, drain and cut broccoli into bite size pieces. Add broccoli, almonds, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve warm with tortilla chips, assorted crackers, bread chunks or fresh vegetable dippers.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; cool and grate.
Mix together grated potatoes, soup, butter, sour cream, onion and cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed flakes or chips.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
(Can be made ahead and frozen but do not bake if you plan to freeze.
To serve next day, store in refrigerator.)

title: spinach with sour cream
directions: Cook the spinach according to package directions.
Drain very well, squeezing out as much liquid as possible.
Meanwhile, melt the butter in a small saucepan and saute the onion and garlic until tender but not browned.
Stir in sour cream, nutmeg, seasoned salt and spinach.
Heat, but do not allow to boil.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: basil tomatoes
directions: Arrange tomato slices, overlapping in ungreased square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inches) or shallow round baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion.
Mix margarine, salt, basil and pepper; drizzle over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven until tomatoes are hot, 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: tunaburgers
directions: Spread mixture on bread.
Bake on baking sheet for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
(Recipe can easily be doubled.)

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat
egg yolks; add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Cook until it boils
and begins to thicken.
Take off heat and add cornstarch mixture.
Beat
until
smooth.
Pour
into	baked
pie crust. Beat
egg whites and 1/2 cup sugar.
Put on top of pie and brown.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Then add flour mix alternately with bananas, a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Bake in greased 8 1/2 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan at 250° about 45 minutes.
Cool before slicing.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix in bowl and bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes in greased and lightly floured pan (13 x 9-inch).

title: pickled cucumbers with red onions
directions: Place sliced cucumbers on rimmed baking sheet, sprinkle with salt.
Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours.
Drain.
Whisk vinegar and sugar until well dissolved.
Add cucumbers, parsley, and onions to mixture.
Season with freshly ground pepper.
Toss to blend.
Let stand at least 2 hours and up to 8.
Transfer to serving dish.
Makes 16 servings.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix together grated cheese, drained tuna, onion, milk and soup. Pour over cooked, drained noodles; mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish; sprinkle with more grated cheese, crushed potato chips and paprika.
Cook in moderate oven until cheese is bubbly and browned.

title: chicken a l'orange
directions: Dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper (put into Ziploc bag to blend and coat).
Brown lightly in oil; remove to casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in skillet.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Cover tightly.
(May be refrigerated at this point until one hour before serving.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand thoroughly together. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: my mother's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix, roll and cut.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: toffee ice cream cake
directions: Tear cake into bite-size pieces.
Mix with Cool Whip and spread on bottom of pan (9 x 13-inches).
Top with ice cream. Sprinkle Heath bars on top.
Freeze.
Let set out for 10 to 20 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put milk and butter in bowl.
Place in microwave and heat. Separate eggs in two bowls.
Mix egg yolks, 1 1/2 cups sugar and cocoa together.
Add warm milk and butter mixture; beat well.
Mix cornstarch with little water and add to mixture.
Cook in microwave until thick.
Take out and mix with mixer for 1 minute. Add vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla until stiff peaks.
Put on top of pie.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper; spread on plate.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth; pour on top of beef mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes more, or until knife comes out clean.

title: dill butter fish with mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in butter or oleo in a skillet. Place fish in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with dill weed, lemon peel, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Pour mushroom mixture over fish.
Makes two servings.

title: leslie's rice casserole
directions: Melt butter, bouillon and water.
Mix in soup and rice.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and add mushrooms. Bake 25 to 30 more minutes, uncovered.

title: better than cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions using milk instead of water.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan according to directions.
Boil sugar and pineapple, pour over hot cake.
Let cool completely. Cream the cream cheese with mixer, slowly add the milk and pudding package.
Spread over cake, let cool in refrigerator until pudding is set.
Layer on cake the remaining ingredients starting with bananas, then Cool Whip, chopped nuts, coconut, then chopped cherries.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: Place meat on large piece of heavy-duty foil.
Spread undiluted cream of mushroom soup over meat.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Wrap in foil, sealing with double fold.
Place seam side up in large baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
When done, lift roast from foil, slice pot roast and place in casserole.
Spoon some gravy over meat.
Dilute if gravy is too thick.
Serve with mashed potatoes, rice or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Put pretzels on cookie sheet.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour the mixture over the pretzels.
Bake at 225° for 20 minutes; stir every 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Mix together pumpkin, sugar, milk, eggs,
nutmeg, allspice, cinnamon, and ginger together and put into ungreased 9x13 pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: apple breakfast popover
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the egg whites, milk, flour, butter and salt until smooth.
Pour into an 8 inch baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until golden and puffed.
Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, combine the apples, (I use Granny Smith) jelly, water and cinnamon.
Heat over low heat until jelly is melted and mixture is heated through.
Cut popover into quarters.
Top each quarter with apple mixture and sprinkle confectionary sugar over the top.

title: cape may cinnamon cheese casserole
directions: Cook in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great for lazy Saturday morning breakfast.

title: quick and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

Spoon peach filling into an 8 or 9-inch square pan. Stir together biscuit mix, milk, sugar and margarine with fork until blended; drop by spoonfuls on top of filling. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm! Preparation time: 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and cover with topping.

title: blueberry golden puffs
directions: Stir with a fork until thoroughly mixed.
Fold in blueberries last.
Drop by teaspoonfuls (too large puffs will not cook through) into deep fat or oil at 375°.
Fry until golden brown (about 3 minutes).
Drain on absorbent paper.
Roll warm puff in cinnamon and sugar or powdered sugar.
Eat warm.

title: supper on a bun
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and French bread in a large bowl.
Cut French bread horizontally to make two halves and place on a cookie sheet.
Spread half of mixture on each half of French bread and top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Feeds 20.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients; beat well.
Drop by teaspoon onto preheated (medium heat) waffle iron for 1 minute, or until done.
Will not stick to waffle iron when lid is lifted.
Spray a little Pam on iron, just in case.
Cool; ice with favorite frosting.

title: tea punch
directions: Add ice and water to taste.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape into meatballs.
Melt margarine in a large skillet; brown and cook meatballs.
Remove from pan; keep warm.
Pour off grease.

title: mystery vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Serve with cucumber, carrot and celery sticks.
Yields about 3 cups.

title: potato soup(crock-pot or stove top)
directions: Place everything except milk in crock-pot.
Cook on low 10 to 12 hours (or overnight) and on high 4 to 5 hours. Stir in milk just before serving.
Use less milk for thicker soup.

title: range cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together, then add to first mixture. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: marci's fruit salad
directions: Beat together the pudding and buttermilk.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Drain the canned fruit thoroughly.
Fold it, the bananas and 1/2 the vanilla wafers (crushed) into the pudding mixture. Pour into a serving dish and garnish the top with the remaining vanilla wafer crumbs.

title: tuna and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles and vegetables according to directions on package.
Add the soup, milk and tuna.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Bake in casserole at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Roll pork chops in mixture.
Have skillet ready with 3 Tbsp Crisco (hot).
Brown pork chops, turn heat down to simmer.
Add 1 1/2 c water.
Cover and simmer for 40 to 45 minutes.
Add rest of dry ingredients in a different skillet.
Brown flour stir constantly.
Add 2/3 c half and half milk to browned flour and pour into skillet with pork chops.
Stir until well mixed with water and chops.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes longer or until pork chops are tender.
Can add water as needed.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters and combine bread crumbs with margarine. Alternate layers of crackers, then oysters, then liquid from oysters.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Combine milk and salt and pour over oysters.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and save. In bacon grease, blend flour, sugar and salt. Stir in tomatoes. Cook, stirring, until thick. Layer hominy, onion rings and tomato mixture in a 2-quart baking dish. Bake, covered, in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: lemonade
directions: Mix sugar, lemonade, and lemon juice together with 1 gal water. Throw lemon rinds into jug after squeezing, for taste and attractiveness.

title: yellow squash soup
directions: Cook squash and onions in chicken broth for 15 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
Add pepper and yogurt.
Puree soup in blender.
Serve hot or cold.
Additional yogurt and pepper may be added.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: impossible seafood pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Mix crab, cheese, onions and pimento in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender or 1 minute by hand).
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edges comes out clean, approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, eggs, butter, water and vanilla until creamy.
Sift salt and baking soda with flour.
Add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Add nuts, coconut, chopped raisins (optional) and oats.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion and butter together until onion is soft.
In large casserole dish, combine onion and butter mixture with all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
This is a large recipe. You may need 2 casserole dishes.
This can become a main dish by adding the chicken to the mixture.

title: marianne's chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter, add water (enough to steam). Add oregano and other spices. Steam (boiling hard) about 20 min. Add mushrooms and broccoli, steam about 30 min more.
Serve with rice. It's Great!
Serves 2.

title: polynesian fruit punch
directions: Combine all juices in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and ice cubes.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: italian chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together water, rice, tomatoes, cheese, onions and 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and remaining 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Melt butter in microwave dish. Add small cubed potatoes (3 small). Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper. Cover and cook 20 minutes in microwave.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients (except chow mein noodles).
Store in refrigerator.
Right before serving, toss in the chow mein noodles.
Serve on bed of lettuce.
Garnish with fruit.

title: zucchini puffs *
directions: *If making for pesach, substitute matzo products to achieve desired consistency.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Stir in sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to boil stirring constantly.
Continue to boil without stirring for 4 minutes.
Remove from stove and stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn.
Mix well.
Divide in 2 large shallow baking pan.
Bake 1 hour at 250° stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Break apart and store in tightly covered container.

title: winter casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown meat; add onion and cook until tender. Stir in milk and cream cheese until well blended.
Add noodles and all remaining ingredients, tossing lightly, until evenly distributed.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tangy cranberry punch
directions: Stir together fruit juices, water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Just before serving, pour over ice in punch bowl. Add ginger ale and garnish with fruit slices.
Makes 10 servings.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon in large soup pot over low heat until almost crisp. Remove; add veggies and garlic.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add seasonings.
Sweet talk someone into hand opening chowder clams, saving juice.
If no luck, steam clams open in separate pot with 2 cups water.
Remove from shells and chop.
Add water to broth to measure 2 quarts (strain broth through cheesecloth first, if needed).
Add the clams, juice and rest of ingredients and cook gently uncovered about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.

title: gazpacho
directions: Mix ingredients, cover and chill thoroughly.
This is low in calories and especially good in the summer with the fresh vegetables in season.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: flan with cream cheese
directions: Prepare caramel by slowly heating sugar in metal container. When golden in color, pour into a mold for the oven (meat loaf pan size is adequate).
Beat egg whites separately.
Beat egg yolks. Add condensed milk while mixing.
Add whole milk and vanilla. (Can do this with hand mixer or even blender.)
Finally, mix in cream cheese and pour into caramel mold.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes by putting into a bigger mold with water.
Tastes great!

title: pizzas
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water in large mixing bowl.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes.
Add salt, sugar, oil and seasoning.
Mix.
Add flour to make stiff dough.
Let stand while making sauce.
Divide dough into 3 balls.
Roll out to make crust for 3 (13-inch) pans of pizza.
Spread with sauce.
Crumble ground beef over dough and/or any other topping that you prefer.
Top with grated cheese or thin sliced Mozzarella.

title: chili mac
directions: Brown hamburger meat in a large skillet. Precook noodles (DO NOT OVERCOOK). Mix remaining ingredients, then pour the mixture over the hamburger. Drain noodles and add to meat mixture. Continue to cook until heated thoroughly. Great when served with a salad and corn muffins.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in an ungreased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Cook, uncovered, at 350° until done, 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: heath bars
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil and butter generously.
Line with graham crackers or saltines.
Meanwhile, melt butter and add brown sugar.
Cook approximately 3 minutes, until well mixed.
Pour over crackers and bake for 5 minutes at 425°.
Remove from oven and pour chocolate chips over hot cracker mixture.
Allow to melt and spread evenly.
Allow to set overnight before cutting.

title: mystery cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil; grease. Line with soda crackers (40). Melt the butter (no substitute) and brown sugar. Boil for 3 minutes. Pour over crackers. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes (until crackers float). Sprinkle the chocolate chips and spread until melted. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Cool and cut.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, except potato chips and cheese.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and potato chips. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, until brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cooked oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix together the flour, salt and baking powder; set aside. Beat the egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Cream the butter and sugar together.
Beat the egg yolks thoroughly; add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in the oatmeal and the milk, then add the dry ingredients that have been mixed together.
Lastly, fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes, or until tops are browned and a pick inserted into a muffin comes out without batter clinging to it.

title: pumpkin delight(or sweet potato delight)
directions: Mix first six ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan which has been sprayed with Pam or equivalent.
Take 2 cups yellow cake mix and spoon evenly over the pumpkin mix.
Melt butter and drizzle over the top of the cake mix covering.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool. Refrigerate before cutting.
Cut into squares.
Serve with whipped cream (Cool Whip).

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Layer chips, sauce and then cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: chicken chip bake
directions: Combine chicken, celery, mayonnaise, almonds, lemon juice, onion and salt.
Pile chicken mixture lightly in 8 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch round ovenware cake dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, then potato chips.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat corn and milk.
Stir in egg.
Stir in cracker crumbs, onion, pimento, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle more cracker crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet. Add chopped chilies, soups and enchilada sauce. Cook until well mixed.
Place 1/2 tortillas on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with half of meat mixture.
Then put in rest of tortillas and meat mixture.
Cover with grated cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Combine water, potatoes, onion, carrots, celery and bouillon. When starts to boil, add broccoli.
Meanwhile, mix and melt together 1/2 cup margarine, 2 cups milk and 1 tablespoon dry mustard.
Pour into vegetables and add 1/2 to 1 pound Velveeta cheese, cut into cubes.
Stir until melted.
(Better if served as soon as cheese melts.)

title: christmas fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Begin timing when the mixture bubbles.)
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir briskly until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan and sprinkle with candy.
Cool thoroughly until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: hungarian pork paprika
directions: Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Place pork cubes in bag and shake to coat with mixture.
In skillet, brown meat in hot oil.
Stir in tomatoes.
Cook, covered, over medium heat 25 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove pan from heat.
Remove cup of sauce mix from skillet and blend with sour cream.
Return mix to pan and blend well.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked chicken in casserole dish.
Pour soup over chicken.
Moisten stuffing with enough broth to hold it together. Spread stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: baked mullet
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Skin fillets.
Place in a single layer in a greased baking dish, 12 x 8-inch.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and pepper.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove from fat and crumble. Cook onion in bacon fat until tender.
Remove from fat and arrange onion evenly over fillets.
Combine bacon, bread crumbs and parsley.
Sprinkle mixture over fillets.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: molasses sugar cookies(gingersnaps)
directions: Melt shortening.
Cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Press with granulated sugar on a glass.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: healthy german skillet dinner
directions: Brown meat; drain on paper towel.
Rinse sauerkraut and drain. Add all ingredients together in skillet and mix well.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes over low heat.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter and chips.
Remove from heat and stir in eggs, sugar, pecans and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool before serving.
(I have found that this is better to cook a day prior to serving.)

title: smokey mountain toffee bars
directions: Mix butters and sugar in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Place the graham cracker halves laid out on ungreased cookie sheet.
Pour hot mixture over these.
Immediately top with chopped pecans.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes at 350°.
When done, remove immediately onto aluminum foil.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Place butter in bottom of cake pan and melt.
Pour brown sugar evenly over butter.
Pour pineapple over brown sugar.
After mixing cake mix, pour your cake batter over pineapple.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Combine in a large casserole dish the first 3 ingredients. Sprinkle Parmesan over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Use sauce to cover when serving.

title: lemon rice and broccoli
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish, mix all but broccoli.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, until tender.
Cook broccoli; drain well. Put rice in a bowl.
Make a well and put broccoli in center, then serve.

title: grandma's pancakes(jamie's favorite)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture should be on the thin side.
Put small amount of oil in frying pan.
When hot, pour in small amounts of batter.
After bubbles appear all over pancakes, flip.

title: lynda's lemon bars
directions: Mix on low speed until crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until light golden brown.

title: cool summer salad
