directions: Pour cottage cheese in bowl. Add Jell-O. Stir. Add pineapple. Stir. Fold in Cool Whip until smooth. Refrigerate if possible before serving.

title: party sausage balls
directions: In a bowl combine all ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.
Yield: about 100 balls.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Add sugar.
Add other ingredients. Let set in warm place one hour.
Punch down.
Put in greased muffin pan.
Let rise in warm place one hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain pears and warm juice.
Mash pears and set aside.
Add enough water to juice to make one cup liquid.
Heat and add jello, stirring until dissolved.

title: judy's date nut balls
directions: Combine all but cereal and flavorings.
Cook 10 minutes in a deep saucepan on medium stirring constantly.
Do not overcook. Remove from heat, stir in cereal and flavorings.
Set aside to cool.

title: zucchini and chicken
directions: In an ovenproof saucepan or casserole, brown chicken pieces in oil and saute over medium heat for about 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, paprika, garlic and herbs.
Pour zucchini-tomato mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: spiced beets
directions: Drain beets; reserve liquid.
Combine all ingredients, except beets.
Heat to boiling.
Add beets and heat through.
Serves 6.

title: chicken-vegetable gumbo
directions: Remove tip and stem ends from okra.
Cut okra into 1/4-inch slices and set aside.

title: open house cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese; mix in powdered Tang and dates.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: french toast
directions: In a shallow bowl, beat together eggs, milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Coat bread on both sides with mixture.
Cook in buttered frying pan until lightly browned.
Cookie cutters can be used in fun shapes.
Syrup (maple) optional.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburg (drain off fat).
Dice bacon.
Fry until about half cooked; drain off fat.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Roll in extra powdered sugar.
Can keep in refrigerator.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Bake at 325°.

title: delicious mixed fruit
directions: Note:
For diabetics, use light fruit and sugar-free pudding mix.

title: laura's favorite candy
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add peanut butter and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Blend grape jelly and chili sauce together in casserole dish and set aside.
Mix ground meat, egg, onion, salt and pepper and form into small balls.
Brown in skillet with very little fat. Drain fat and drop browned meatballs in casserole with the sauce. Bake in a 300° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans and drain.
Place in casserole dish and top with warm soup.
Sprinkle cheese on top of soup.
Bake at high degree until cheese is bubbly.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat egg whites to stiff peaks, then add sugar and beat. Then add egg yolks, one by one. Add oil and beat. Sift together flour and baking powder. Add alternately flour mix and chopped apples. Pour batter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and noodle delight
directions: Brown beef.
Drain any fat.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: maple gingerbread
directions: Blend syrup with cream and egg.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into syrup mixture.
Add butter.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch baking pan, lined with greased brown paper.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 375° to 400°.
In skillet or pan, heat shortening; tilt pan to coat skillet and on sides.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, shortening and egg; mix until blended. Pour into hot pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 9 to 10 servings.

title: the best dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese with milk.
Add the sour cream and cottage cheese, blend well.
Add in onions, scallions, garlic and all seasonings.
Chill for 1 hour, add seasonings to your own taste.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Beat all the ingredients together for 5 minutes until light and fluffy.
Refrigerate or freeze until ready to serve.
Makes 30 to 40 servings.

title: pecan meatballs
directions: Cream together cream cheese and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Let set to thicken.
Form balls and bake on lightly oiled cookie sheet in 350° to 400° oven for 30 minutes or until browned (turn after 10 to 15 minutes).
Serves 8 to 10.
This recipe contains 1/2 egg per serving.

title: dirty rice
directions: Wash rice under hot tap water several times until milky water runs clear.
Run some hot water into pot about an inch over rice. Bring to a boil, then put lid on and simmer for about 20 minutes, checking for doneness.
Put chicken livers and gizzards into another pot, covering with water and simmer for about 15 minutes on medium heat.
Add salt, black pepper, cayenne pepper, bell pepper, green onion, half of the chopped onion, garlic and garlic salt, leaving lid off.
Cook for about 20 minutes and then cut up livers and gizzards or grind them up.
Put ground beef into pot, put livers and gizzards back into pot and cook until done.
Don't let all of the juices dry out.
Put remaining onion into pot about 10 minutes before turning pot off.
When finished, stir rice in.
If dry, add a tablespoon of shortening.
Serves 10.

title: candied yams
directions: In large casserole dish, layer margarine in dish.
Drain yams and place in dish.
Use the juice from yams and mix sugar and pineapple together.
Add dash of cinnamon or nutmeg.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rice pilaf with pine nuts
directions: In small heavy saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; saute until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add rice and pine nuts.
Stir until all grains are covered.
Add broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil over low heat and simmer slowly without lifting lid for 25 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add sugar, flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Pour large can of peaches over batter.

title: corn bread fish bake
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Cut fillets into 4 x 1-inch strips; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together the cornmeal, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add onion and chili peppers.
Beat together buttermilk and eggs.
Stir into cornmeal mixture along with shortening.
Spread batter into greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place fish in rows atop batter; press into batter. Stir together butter or margarine and mustard.
Spread over fish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 450° oven 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: vanilla chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually blend into butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: armenian vegie salad
directions: Marinate all overnight in a well flavored French or Italian dressing.
Chill.
May be made 2 days ahead.
Toss gently before serving.
Serves 8.

title: lemon date cake(christmas special)
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, lemon juice and lemon extract. Add 3 cups flour and baking powder. Add dates and nuts with 1 cup of flour. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: deluxe broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on pkg. but less a few minutes. Drain broccoli. In mixing bowl combine flour, soup, sour cream, grated onion, carrots, salt and pepper. Stir in broccoli and pour into a buttered 2 quart casserole. Toss buttered stuffing mix and put around the edge of the casserole. Bake 30-40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: vinegar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sally's lemon squares
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and 1 egg until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup. Press remainder of mix into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cream together cream cheese, lemon juice and 1 egg.
Spread over baked crust and crumble reserved 1 cup of mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pumpkin with apple
directions: Place pumpkin and apple in heavy saucepan. Sprinkle with sugar. Add water, butter and salt.
Cover and cook over moderate heat until pumpkin is tender, stirring occasionally, and adding more water if necessary. Transfer to a heated serving dish. Sprinkle with walnuts and cinnamon.
Makes a great accompaniment to roast turkey, ham or pork.

title: cracker candy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet (with lips) with foil. Place crackers on cookie sheet.
Melt oleo; add sugar.
Boil 1 minute, pour over crackers and bake for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
When melted, spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Whisk juice and dressing mix together.
Marinate breasts in 1/2 juice mixture for 2 to 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: swedish spritz
directions: Thoroughly cream butter and sugar; add egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat
well. Add baking powder to flour; mix. Add
to creamed mixture;
mix until smooth (mixture will pull away	from sides of bowl).
Do not chill.
Force dough through cookie	press onto
cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine the bread, oleo, sugar and eggs.
Mix well; add pineapple and milk.
Mix and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or light brown.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Place cauliflower in shallow baking dish. Combine soup, milk and cheese in a bowl, mixing well.
Pour over cauliflower. Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly. Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make 2 layers of cake.
In punch bowl, crumble one layer of cake.
Pour half of pudding mix over cake.
Crumble other layer of cake and add rest of pudding mix; spread evenly.
Add pineapple. Pour over pudding mix.
Pour cherry pie filling evenly.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: monkey bread #2
directions: Combine 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll each piece in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Grease Bundt pan.
Layer biscuit pieces in Bundt pan. Sprinkle chopped nuts or raisins between each layer.
Cook margarine, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in saucepan on stove.
Boil mixture for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: ice box cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and egg together.
Add dry ingredients and nuts that have been mixed together and blend well. Roll dough into a roll about 2 1/2 to 3 inches in diameter. Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Slice into round cookies about 1/4 inch thick.
Bake on cookie sheet in 400° oven until lightly browned about 7 to 10 minutes.
These cookies are crispy.

title: kay's pie crust and crumb mix
directions: Mix the flour and salt in large mixing bowl; cut Crisco into flour using 2 knives or pastry blender until mixture is uniform and very fine.
Store in a covered container.
No refrigeration is needed.
Makes 7 or 8 cups

title: banana-berry batido
directions: Place all ingredients in blender. Blend on low for 30 seconds, then on high for 30 seconds, until smooth.
Serve in chilled glasses.

title: rolls
directions: Mix cake mix and yeast.
Add salt, flour and warm water.
Mix together and let rise 1 hour.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Put chopped tomatoes, onions and peppers in large pan.
Pour remaining ingredients over tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Fill sterile jars and seal.

title: laura's bruschetta
directions: Marinate the first 5 ingredients in a little olive oil.
Grill fresh Italian or French bread in oven (I use the long French loaves in Southbury Food Market).
Drizzle with olive oil.
Cover bread with marinated vegetables, sprinkle with Mozzarella and broil in oven until bubbly.

title: black-eyed pea soup
directions: Cut up and brown bacon.
Add onion, garlic, tomatoes and jalapeno peppers.
Saute until vegetables are done.
Add drained black-eyed peas, salt, pepper, water and bouillon.
Simmer a short time.
Add grated cheese.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, milk and eggs in a bowl, beating until smooth.
Heat 1/4-inch oil in skillet.
Pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel.
Fry for 1 minute.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: wheat bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cracked wheat, oil and salt.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Add yeast, stirring to dissolve.
Add molasses and malt and stir to combine.
Add brewer's yeast, flours and wheat germ, mixing to form a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface and knead for about 7 minutes, kneading in additional flour, if necessary.
Turn dough into oiled bowl, turning to grease the top.
Cover with plastic wrap and let rise in a warm place for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down and form into a loaf.
Turn into a well-oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf and let rise again for about 30 minutes.
Mist the top with water and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, misting the top with water 15 and 30 minutes into baking.
Remove from pan and let cool on wire rack.

title: perfectly fried chicken
directions: Cut up chicken, cutting breast into 2 to 3 parts. Blend salt, paprika and pepper with flour. Work flour mixture into chicken pieces, leaving no moist spots to splatter and lose juice. Place coated pieces on a rack to dry, if there is time. Use a skillet with a lid or use a chicken fryer. A 9-inch skillet will need 2/3 cup of fat or oil. Heat 1/4-inch of fat or oil in skillet until a drop of water sizzles. Start with meaty pieces first; slip in slimmer parts as meaty pieces brown. Don't crowd pieces. Reduce heat gradually when browning begins. Turn 2 or 3 times with tongs. Never pierce with fork. When chicken is light tan, add 1 to 2 tablespoons of water; cover tightly. Browning will continue. As a guide to doneness, allow 50 to 60 minutes after chicken is covered. For extra crispness, uncover skillet for the last 10 to 12 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine macaroni, cheese, corned beef, soup, milk and celery. Blend well.

Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Toss cubed bread in melted butter and arrange around edge of casserole. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350° until golden brown. Let it stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Beat egg yolks; gradually add sugar, salt, cornstarch, butter and milk.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Cook sliced bananas into shell and add vanilla or rum to custard.
Pour over bananas in shell.

title: busy gardener's stew
directions: Add all ingredients, except green beans,
to crock-pot. Cook on low 6 to 8 hours. Ten minutes before serving, add green beans and turn cooker on high. Cook 10 minutes. Adding green beans last keeps the color green and the beans crisper.

title: guinness stew
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the flour with pepper and salt; mix.
Take the cubed beef and add to the flour.
Cover the beef thoroughly with the flour.
Place the vegetable oil in a frying pan; heat on medium.
Cook the floured beef in the frying pan until all sides are browned.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook ground beef and onion over medium heat until brown. Drain.
Add whole tomatoes, water, bouillon cubes, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and bring to a boil.
Add egg noodles and simmer for another 30 minutes.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: surprise chocolate dessert
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Add sugar and egg yolks; mix thoroughly.
Remove from heat and fold in whipped cream and egg whites.
Tear angel food cake into bite-sized pieces.
Put layer into buttered pan, using half of cake.
Cover with layer of chocolate mixture and repeat.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: raised sugar cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening, eggs, buttermilk and almond. Add salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add flour.
Roll out on floured covered surface to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Ice with favorite cookie icing.

title: meatballs gordon
directions: Start with meat.
Add bread, beat in egg and add breadcrumbs to thicken.
Add chopped onion, garlic and whatever herbs to suit your taste.
In medium saucepan, combine tomato sauce, tomato paste, plus the water (see above).
Add chopped tomato; sprinkle in basil.
Make 1 1/2-inch round meatballs; place in sauce. Simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve with pasta or on sandwiches. . .
whatever.
Best if eaten a day or 2 after preparation.

title: orange butter coffee cake
directions: Soften yeast in warm water, stir in 1/4 cup sugar, salt, eggs, sour cream and 6 tablespoons butter.
Add flour to form stiff dough, beating well.
Cover, let rise until double, about 2 hours. Combine 3/4 cup sugar, 3/4 cup coconut and orange rind.
Knead dough about 15 times, roll half of dough to 12-inch circle.
Brush with melted butter, sprinkle with half of coconut mixture.
Cut in 12 wedges.
Roll up, starting with wide end.
Place rolls, point side down, in 3 rows in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with glaze, sprinkle with 1/4 cup coconut.
Serve warm or cold.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate nut bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine beaten eggs, bananas, vanilla, oil and milk.
Blend well.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams and reserve liquid. Heat butter in large saucepan over medium-low heat. Cook onion until tender. Stir in flour until blended. Add reserved clam liquid, water, potatoes and pepper. Bring to a boil. Lower heat and cook until potatoes are tender. Add clam meat and cook 3 to 5 minutes. Add milk and cook just until heated through.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix potatoes as directed on box.
Add remaining ingredients and spread into a baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Combine
sugar,
shortening, sour milk and baking soda; mix with
vanilla.
Then add flour, cocoa, cinnamon and salt. Beat all together
and
bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° until done.
This is an old recipe.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Thoroughly combine eggs, sugar, margarine, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in coconut.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: granny cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with 1/2 cup pecans and 3/4 cup brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain water off and cool noodles by rinsing under cold water.
Add chopped ingredients and bottled dressing and shake on cheese and mix.

title: hello dollies
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Sprinkle coconut over crumbs. Sprinkle chocolate chips over coconut.
Sprinkle pecans.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over top.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: pumpkin date bread
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, water and pumpkin.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add dates and nuts.
Grease 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Lower temperature is needed for baking time.

title: cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly cream together cheeses and garlic until completely blended.
Refrigerate cheese mixture for approximately 1 hour or until mixture has firmed up.
Split mixture in half and form into balls.
Roll balls in chopped nuts and wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Chill 4-6 hours or overnight, if possible.
Serve with crackers or breadsticks.

title: dan's roast marinade
directions: Cook onion in oil a few minutes, add garlic, celery, chili sauce, catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, lemon juice, horseradish, mustard, smoked salt, Tabasco sauce, and sugar.
Add sherry and simmer 10 minutes.
Use London broil or beef roast of choice.
Marinate overnight or longer.
Bake in marinade until done at usual temperature.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Mix meat with seasoning, crumbs, eggs, chopped vegetables and enough milk to make a moist mixture.
Pack meat loaf mixture into a loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes or until brown. Coat loaf top about halfway through baking period.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Drain tuna.
Combine tuna and mushroom soup over stove until hot.
Add potato chips or chow mein noodles on top.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Coat cereal with chocolate chip mixture in bowl. Then dump coated cereal in powdered sugar; mix well.

title: cucumber-onion salad
directions: Combine cucumber slices, water and 1 tablespoon of salt in bowl.
Let stand for 1 hour; drain.
Add onion rings; set aside. Combine sugar, vinegar, parsley, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper in jar; cover tightly and shake to mix well.
Pour over vegetables; toss gently.
Chill, covered, for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter kisses cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients on waxed paper and set aside. Cream with mixer, margarine, peanut butter and sugars.
Blend in eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls (if dough is too sticky, place in refrigerator for a few minutes.)
Roll each ball in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and press a candy kiss or Brach's star in center.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool on cooling rack.

title: potato salad
directions: Note:
Do not overcook potatoes; leave a little firm.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cook pie crust 6 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Add mixture to pie shell and cook for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fudgy nut squares
directions: In saucepan, combine 3/4 cup margarine and 1/3 cup chocolate chips.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add combined crumbs, coconut and nuts; mix well.
Press onto bottom of ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Chill.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Spread over crust; chill.
Melt remaining margarine and chocolate pieces; spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill.
Cut into squares.

title: date pudding roll
directions: Mix dates, marshmallows and nuts; add milk.
Crush graham crackers and add enough to form mixture into a roll.
Roll, wrap and chill at least 2 hours.

title: squash pie
directions: Melt butter and mix all together. Bake in unbaked pie shell.

title: pretzel salad torte
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Let partially set, then add strawberries.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.

title: western bean casserole
directions: In soup pot, cook bacon just to crispy. Remove from pan and drain grease. Brown ground meat and make crumbly. Add onions and garlic. Drain grease. Turn heat to medium-low. Add pork and beans with liquid, drained kidney beans and lima beans, stirring well. Add Open Pit, chili powder and Worcestershire. Take about 90 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortenings and sugar. Add eggs. Beat for at least 2 minutes, preferably longer. Then add flavoring. Beat well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add remaining ingredients to meat and stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on cocktail rye.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Put in bag and freeze.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes when needed.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel, rinse and cut onions into slices; melt margarine in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add onion and cook slowly until golden.
Blend bouillon and season with salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: date filled sugar cookies
directions: With mixer, whip butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and whip until light in color; add vanilla.
Add salt, baking soda and baking powder to flour.
Blend sour cream and flour mixture alternately to batter with mixer (mix slightly).
Put 1 tablespoon cookie dough on greased cookie sheet.
Smash each cookie on top. Dip fingers in flour and press together edge of each cookie.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 12 minutes or until slightly golden brown (sprinkle sugar on top before baking and can put walnut half in middle of each cookie).

title: dieter's emerald cloud dessert
directions: Prepare Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water to dissolve; add soda pop.
Blend 1/2 cup crushed pineapple with the ripe banana in blender.
Add this to the Jell-O along with the remaining pineapple.
Chill to the soft set stage.

title: tarantula cookies
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Pour noodles and peanuts in morsel mix.
Drop on wax paper.
May put in freezer for a few minutes to harden a little.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil fryer in enough water to make 8 cups broth; cool.
Strip chicken from bone, cutting into small strips.
Discard skin.
In large saucepan over low heat, stir flour and oil until smooth, stirring often, 30 minutes or until mixture turns dark brown.
Stir in onion, celery, green pepper and garlic; cook 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, okra, bay leaf, salt, thyme, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add chicken broth.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Add chicken.
Discard bay leaf.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: grilled orange roughy with sauce
directions: Mix and marinate fish in mixture turning every 30 minutes for about 4 hours. Grill the fish.

title: grandma judi's zesty jalapeno fish fillets
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 2 minutes; add zucchini and cook 2 minutes more or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Drain.
Cover; keep warm. Spray nonstick coating onto the cold rack of broiler pan.
Place fish on an unheated rack.
Season with salt and pepper.
Measure thickness of fish.
Broil fish 4 inches from heat, just until it flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Allow 4 to 6 minutes per 1/2 inch of thickness.

title: bunsteads
directions: Fill 6 hot dog buns generously.
Wrap separately in foil. Bake in slow oven at 250° to 300° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: korean salad
directions: Put oil, catsup, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and onion in blender.
Mix spinach, water chestnuts and bean sprouts.
Pour over the dressing.
Cook bacon crisp and crumble over salad.
Slice the hard-boiled eggs.
Mix and toss.

title: micro spicy beef dip(microwave)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, saute ground beef, onion and garlic 4 to 6 minutes, stirring twice.
Spoon off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, oregano and sugar.
Cover and cook 5 to 6 minutes, stirring twice.
Add cream, Parmesan and cream cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Makes 3 cups.

title: great christmas punch
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Float orange sherbet on top. Serves a crowd.

title: southern fried catfish
directions: In pie plate or shallow dish, combine cornmeal, salt and peppers.
Dredge fish pieces in cornmeal mixture, patting to coat on all sides.
In a large, heavy skillet, heat about 1/2 inch of oil to 375° or until a small piece of bread sizzles when dropped in.
Add fish fillets and fry until golden brown, about 4 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels.

title: swedish almond toast
directions: Cream the butter and oleo. Add sugar and mix well. Beat in eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and nuts and mix in alternately with half and half. Stir in extract.
Grease a 5 x 9-inch pan. Cut wax paper to fit pan.
Re-grease wax paper.
Pour in pan and bake at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Take out of pan and refrigerate overnight. Slice like toast.
Dry in oven at 250° for 15 to 30 minutes; halfway through, turn slices.

title: cabbage-pineapple salad
directions: Grate cabbage and mix all ingredients together (a very good salad).

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix with spoon and drop on a greased baking sheet.

title: plantation spoon bread
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Gradually stir in cornmeal and cook until thickened.
Add butter, salt, molasses and baking powder.
Slowly add hot mixture to well beaten eggs.
Stir constantly.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 45 minutes.
Serve at once.
Serves 8.

title: hot sausage
directions: Slice sausage up and lightly brown in skillet, then add a can of nacho cheese soup to skillet.
Simmer over low heat until warm.

title: orange balls
directions: Orange juice and butter must be soft and at room temperature. Crush vanilla wafers and add to the softened mixture.
Stir.
Add sugar and nuts.
Roll into bite size balls, then roll in coconut.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla.
Place in flat dish (pie dish). Cover with chopped peanuts. Dip in apple slices.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch, then all other ingredients. Bake in buttered 1 1/2-quart dish at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Chop cranberries and mix with 1/4 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in oleo.
In a separate bowl, beat egg.
Add milk and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients just until blended. Fold in cranberries.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken curry
directions: In a large skillet or dutch oven, bring 1/2 cup chicken stock to a boil.
Add chicken, onions, potatoes and green pepper.
Cook over medium heat until chicken is opaque (3 to 5 minutes).
Stir in remaining stock and other ingredients and heat to boiling; lower heat and simmer uncovered until the vegetables are tender (about 30 to 45 minutes).
Remove cinnamon stick.
Stir raisins or apples through before serving.
Serve on rice or couscous with condiments. Serves 6.

title: strawberry fudge balls
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed until creamy.
Add melted chocolate and beat until smooth.
Stir in wafer crumbs and preserves.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape into balls; roll in chopped almonds and chill.
You may freeze fudge balls up to 2 months.
Put single layer on cookie sheet to freeze, then into Ziploc freezer bags.
Make a day ahead and put into mini paper liners and chill until ready to serve.
Raspberry preserves could be substituted for strawberry.

title: twenty-four hour fruit salad
directions: Cook until thick, eggs, sugar, cream and lemons.
Whip cream and fold into cooked sauce.
Then add to fruit and marshmallows. Let set 24 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: fantasy fudge(microwave)
directions: Microwave margarine in a bowl on high 1 minute.
Add sugar and milk, mix well.
Microwave on high 5 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Mix well, scrape bowl.
Microwave 5 1/2 minutes stir after 3 minutes.
Stir in choc. chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 13x9 inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large frying pan and saute onions and broccoli and heat until thawed.
Cut cheese over broccoli.
Let it melt and stir everything together.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes until lightly brown.
Let set at least 30 minutes (or longer).
Can be mixed the day before and put in refrigerator and then bake.

title: layered salad
directions: Put all the ingredients in a large, deep bowl in the order given.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir the ingredients together until well mixed.
(Add more mayonnaise, only after mixing well, if needed.)

title: hot cottage potato salad
directions: Mix all together, except oleo and milk, and season with salt and pepper.
Place in 3-quart baking dish.
Pour oleo and milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream of potato leek soup
directions: Pare and dice the potatoes and leeks (use some green of the leeks).
Bring the chicken broth to a boil.
Add the potatoes and leeks.
Bring to second boil and cook, covered, 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Put in blender and puree.
Return to saucepan and add the butter, salt, white pepper and light cream. Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Do not boil.
Garnish with 2 tablespoons snipped chives and 1/4 teaspoon paprika. Serve hot.

title: cheddar cheese straws
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is coarse crumbs.
Stir in cheese and 1/2 cup ice water just until mixture forms a soft dough and leaves the side of the bowl.
On a lightly floured surface, pat the dough into a 6 x 6-inch square.
Wrap with plastic wrap and freeze for 30 minutes. On a slightly floured surface, roll chilled dough into an 18 x 8-inch rectangle.
Starting from the 8-inch side, fold 1/3 of dough over the middle third; fold opposite 1/3 over both and make a 6 x 8-inch rectangle.
Repeat rolling and folding as in the before step.
Wrap and freeze 30 minutes again.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and 1 cup pecans.
Roll into ball and roll ball in reserved cup of pecans.

title: neiman's cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flours, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir in chocolates and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheets.
Bake 6 minutes.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: tuna-stuffed potatoes
directions: Brush potatoes with fat.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Cut in half lengthwise; scoop out pulp and mash.
Add salt, pepper, butter and milk; beat until fluffy.
Stir in tuna.
Refill potato shells.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Return to oven for 10 minutes at 450°.
Makes 8.

title: bacon broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli according to microwave directions, until tender-crisp, about 9-10 minutes.
In large bowl mix together well drained broccoli, carrot and red onion.
In class measuring cup, combine vinegar, sugar and oil.
Microwave on high 2 minutes. Pour over vegetable mixture and mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve warm or chilled, with crumbled bacon on top.

title: ten dollar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in Pyrex bowl. In separate bowl, mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Spoon fruit over batter. Bake 45 minutes.
This is easy and oh so scrumptious!

title: special breakfast
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch pan or casserole, solidly line with bread.
Top with ham, cheese and dots of Velveeta cheese over sharp cheese.
Cover with remaining bread; slowly ladle liquid over bread.
Cover with Saran Wrap; refrigerate overnight.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a large glass bowl.
Add milk and butter.
Do not stir.
Cook at High in microwave for 4 1/2 to 6 minutes or until butter is melted.
Take out and add nuts and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Spread into greased 12 x 8-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: dirt dessert
directions: You will need a new, clean clay or plastic flower pot and a new garden trowel and a bouquet of plastic flowers.

title: bacon and cheese bread
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside. Combine eggs, milk and oil; add to oat mixture, stirring just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in water for a few minutes to soften.
Mix 2 tablespoons soup with rest of ingredients.
Divide mixture among cabbage leaves; fold in sides.
Roll up and secure with toothpick. In skillet, place roll, seam side down.
Pour on soup.
Cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Stir now and then.
Spoon sauce over rolls.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain well.
In a large kettle, combine beef and all ingredients.
Cook until all the vegetables are tender.
Serve with hot corn bread.

title: creole chicken nuggets
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Dip chicken in mixture, coating well.
Heat oil in skillet.
Cook chicken until tender and golden; drain on paper towels.

title: fresh-squeezed lemonade
directions: Combine water and sugar in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil and cook one minute.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Pour sugar mixture into a pitcher; chill.
Add lemon juice to sugar mixture; stir well.
Serve over ice and garnish with lemon wedges, if desired.

title: chicken casserole(mamie's favorite)
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Chop into bite size pieces. Combine chicken, sour cream and soup and pour into greased casserole dish. Crush crackers and sprinkle over top. Drizzle with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eggless white cake
directions: Cream
butter;
add
sugar, flour and milk alternately. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cornbread taco bake
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn, green pepper and tomato sauce.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.

title: holiday party punch
directions: Use large punch bowl and an ice ring.
This makes 25 to 30 (8-ounce) servings.

title: haluski
directions: Simmer sliced onions in butter, while noodles are cooking and cabbage is steaming.
Cool cabbage and slice or chunk.
Mix with noodles and onions.
Add more butter.

title: beef casserole
directions: Melt shortening. Add onions and cook slowly until golden brown.
Add meat; brown, stirring frequently.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder, tomato soup and corn; mix well.
Turn into well-greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to package.
Fill paper cups in muffin pans 2/3 full.
In separate bowl mix cream cheese with sugar. Beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate bits.
Drop one teaspoon of cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake as package directs. Makes about 39 cupcakes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw and mash up the Tater Tots.
Mix in sour cream, chicken soup and shredded cheese, then melt and mix in margarine.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown. Salt and pepper to taste (optional).

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake as package directs. Making 2 layers.
Cool and split into 4 layers. Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Blend well.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Rinse cans out with small amount of water.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a baking dish deep enough to prevent bubbling over edges.
Place chicken on top and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Test chicken and rice for doneness.
(Do not use instant rice.)

title: brown rice surprise
directions: In 5-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot oil, cook onions and green peppers until tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken and 1/4 teaspoon salt to onion mixture over high heat; cook until chicken loses its pink color, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes with their liquid, ham, parsley, hot sauce, thyme and 1 cup water.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in rice; reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 55 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jean's date nut bread
directions: Place nuts, dates, baking soda, salt and shortening in bowl. Pour boiling water over ingredients.
Let set.
Mix eggs, vanilla, sugar and flour together.
Add to date, nut mixture.
Mix only enough to combine all ingredients.
Put into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan and bake for one hour in 350° oven.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Bake pretzels, sugar and butter (mixed) for 8 minutes at 400° in 9 x 13-inch loaf pan, then cool.
Stir cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar well and spread over cooled pretzels.
Cook jello, water and strawberries until syrupy and pour over cream layer. Refrigerate overnight.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan as listed, ending with bacon on top.
Best if covered and refrigerated for a couple of hours before serving.

title: candied fruit slices
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add powdered sugar, creaming well. Blend in unbeaten egg and vanilla.
Add flour; mix well.
Stir in pecan halves and candied cherries; cut in halves.
Chill for 1 hour.
Divide dough into thirds.
Shape into rolls.
Wrap in wax paper; chill at least 3 hours.
For quick chilling, place in freezer for 1 hour.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 13 to 15 minutes until delicately browned on edges.
Can use half red cherries and half green cherries.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Pour in stock and milk, gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook slowly until slightly thickened.
Season with salt.
Add diced chicken, sliced mushrooms, green pepper and pimientos.
Blend in the egg yolk and sherry.
Cook until thick.
Serve on Puff Pastry Shells.

title: banana bread #1
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add oil.
Beat 10 minutes. Add cinnamon and bananas.
Add soda to buttermilk. Stir and add to creamed mixture.
Add flour.
Pour into three greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool and wrap.
Can be frozen.

title: chocolate pretzel crunch
directions: In
a microwave-safe bowl, combine morsels and shortening. Microwave,	uncovered,
for
2 minutes on High, stirring once during cooking.

title: spinach pie
directions: Filling:
Cook frozen spinach according to package directions, then squeeze out as much water from spinach as possible.
Stir together spinach, cream cheese, Feta, Parmesan and pepper.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix and bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Continue to boil and stir until mixture thickens.
It should be thick enough to stand on biscuits.
Serve hot over hot biscuits.

title: sweet 'n' sour chicken on rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine soy sauce, honey, vinegar, thyme, paprika, cayenne pepper, allspice and pepper in a shallow baking dish, mix well. Pierce both sides of each breast with a fork. Place in baking dish. Using tongs, turn chicken several times to coat. Bake chicken, basting several times with sauce, for 30 minutes. Spoon cooked rice onto a serving platter. Arrange chicken over rice. Drizzle a small amount of sauce over chicken. Serve remaining sauce on the side. Serves four.

title: magnificent meats
directions: Butter the baking dish thoroughly.
Lightly salt the bottom of the dish with seasoned salt.
Butter and use seasoned salt on both sides of the meat; place in a baking dish.
Cover and cook at 250° for about 3 hours.
Comes out tender and juicy.

title: beef tip
directions: Cream the cream cheese and milk; stir in beef, then blend in pepper, garlic salt, sour cream and onion flakes.
Place in a square baking dish.
To prepare topping, saute pecans in butter and salt.
Pour over beef and cheese mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp.
Rinse lightly.
While draining mix all other ingredients together and add shrimp.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or bagels.
Makes large bowl.
Enjoy!

title: christmas hot punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to boil and let simmer 1 hour.
Gets better when reheated.
Serves 30.

title: turkey patty with sweet sour pineapple sauce
directions: Mix together turkey, water chestnuts, garlic and soy sauce in medium bowl.
Shape into 4 one-half inch thick patties.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add patties and cook 10 to 12 minutes or until no longer pink, turning once.
Serve with Sweet Sour Pineapple Sauce.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Put all ingredients in boiler and bring to a boil. Roll out canned biscuits and put 1/2 apple in dough. Arrange in pan and pour liquid over biscuits and apples. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in the boiling water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put in mold.

title: crumb dessert
directions: Mix sugar, crumbs, vanilla, dates, walnuts and baking powder. Then beat the egg yolks and add to the mixture.
Beat the egg whites and fold into the mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and crumble it up.
Place into plastic bag or container.
Refrigerate.
Serve under ice cream.

title: date roll cookies
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, dates and margarine in saucepan.
Boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add vanilla, nuts and cereal; stir.
While warm, shape into balls the size of walnuts and roll in coconut.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all the ingredients until well blended.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender; combine rest of ingredients and add to vegetables (you can put some of the cheese and onion rings on top during the last 5 minutes of baking).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the shortening and sugar, then add molasses and egg.
Mix well, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice potatoes.
Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables; i.e., carrots, celery, cucumber, broccoli, cherry tomatoes and cauliflower.

title: apple and ? pie filling crisp
directions: Cut apples with peeling on into pieces or slices and top with the pie filling of your choice.
Sprinkle with Streusel Topping. Prepare in 1-quart microwavable dish.

title: fried green plantains
directions: Choose a plantain with yellow-green or all-green peel that is hard to the touch.
Remove peel and slice in about 1 inch perpendicular slices.
If it is too difficult to remove the peel, first cut off the ends and then make 4 end-to-end cuts through the peel only and gently lift and roll off the peel.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Combine Crisco, salt and flavorings.
Continue beating while very gradually adding water until completely mixed.
Add powdered sugar a little at a time and whip at top speed about 5 minutes until creamy consistency.
Use at room temperature.

title: marinated chicken with peppers and rice
directions: Place chicken pieces in roasting pan; sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Pour white wine over the chicken.
Also, dissolve the chicken bouillon cube in a cup of boiling water; pour over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Separately stir-fry peppers and prepare 1 cup of instant white rice.

title: jellied tuna fish salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water, vinegar and salt.
Chill.
When slightly thickened, fold in remaining ingredients.
Blend.
Turn into individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Unfold on crisp lettuce.
Garnish with additional mayonnaise.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Stew chicken until done; save broth.
Grease dish well.
Chop chicken into bite size pieces.
Line dish with tortillas dipped in broth.
Put layer of chicken, cheese, bell pepper and onion and a layer of soup and sour cream, mixed together.
Sprinkle with chili powder and use 1/2 of Ro-Tel tomatoes; repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Cover with foil and cook 50 minutes at 325°; uncover and cook another 10 minutes.
You can use leftover broth in casserole.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, mix 1/2 cup of onion rings with soup, sour cream and Worcestershire sauce.
Fold in the beans.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Top with remaining onions. Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Make cream sauce with butter, flour, milk and salt.
Add cooked spinach when cool.
Stir in yolks; fold in egg whites. Pour into buttered casserole.
Place in pan of hot water; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Nice served with cheese or mushroom sauce. Serves 6.

title: glogg nog
directions: Beat eggs on low speed of electric mixer until blended.
Add sugar and spices.
Beat at medium speed until sugar is dissolved. On low speed beat in softened ice cream.
Add the juices.
Cover and chill.
To serve, pour the ice cream mixture into a large bowl (punch bowl).
Slowly pour in ginger ale, stirring with an up and down motion.
Makes 17 cups.

title: smothered steak crock-pot
directions: Put steak strips, flour and salt in crock-pot.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Cook on high 1 hour, then for 8 hours on low or 5 hours on high.
Serve over rice.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Place cooked meat in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle on chopped onions.
Pour chicken soup over meat and onions.
Place tater tots over mixture until covered.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter clay(edible)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add more milk (dry) if necessary to make a pliable dough.

title: eggnog cranberry salad
directions: In saucepan, combine vanilla pudding, lemon gelatin and 4 cups of water.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Stir in lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
In separate saucepan, dissolve raspberry gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Beat in cranberry sauce.
Fold in nuts and celery.
Chill until partially set.

title: grandma's gingersnaps
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Let cool.
Add other ingredients and stir thoroughly.
Chill for several hours.
Roll into balls, then roll in sugar.
Do not press down! Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crunch bars
directions: Cream together butter or oleo, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix together flour, baking powder and cocoa.
Add flour mixture to the egg mixture; mix well.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and spoon over top of mixture:
1 pint of Marshmallow Creme or 2 cups miniature marshmallows; bake for 3 minutes more.
Remove from oven.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Spread over bars.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: lime chiffon pie
directions: Combine the limeade and milk; fold in dessert topping and pour into baked pie shells.
Chill 4 hours or more.
May use freezer peaches or strawberries instead of limeade.

title: old fashioned custard ice cream
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed.
Stir sugar and flour together and add to eggs.
Add milnot and 3 cups milk and beat until well blended.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring oleo, water and cocoa to a boil in 3-quart boiler. Remove from stove and add sugar and flour.
Mix together eggs, sour cream, vanilla and soda.
Add to cocoa mixture until just combined.
Pour on cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave chunky applesauce
directions: Peel,
core and quarter enough apples to fill a 5 quart microwavable casserole dish.
Add 1/4 cup of water.
Microwave on High for 35 minutes until
tender.
Stir in sugar to taste. Add vanilla.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter pan first, then mix both chicken soup and celery soup with 3/4 cup chicken broth from cooked chicken.
Put a layer of chicken, then soup over chicken, then a layer of dressing mix. Repeat the layers.
Cover with approximately 1/2 to 1 cup of chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon or chocolate delight
directions: Mix together flour, butter and nuts.
Pat evenly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Blend in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over baked crust.
Beat pudding mix and milk 2 minutes.
Spread over cheese layer.
Chill to set.
Spread with rest of Cool Whip. Sprinkle top with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: pasta with white beans, tomatoes and basil
directions: Saute olive oil and garlic in skillet over very low heat until garlic begins to sizzle and turns golden, about 2 minutes.
Add beans, tomatoes, basil and salt and pepper to taste.
Remove from heat.

title: pretzel treats
directions: Preheat oven to 175 degrees.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam. Unwrap kisses.
Put pretzels on cookie sheet and place a Hershey Kiss in the middle of each pretzel.
Bake at 175 degrees for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place an M & M in the center of each kiss, pushing it down just a little.
Let cool for 6 - 8 hours or until kiss is hard again.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
When almost done, add onion and finish cooking meat until done.
Add chili powder, cumin and flour.
Mix well and add 1 1/2 cups of water. Simmer on medium heat about 2 minutes.
Add chili and simmer. Grate 1 to 1 1/2 cups American cheese or any soft cheese.
Soften tortillas in hot grease.
Dip part of the cooked meat out of the chili.
Roll meat and cheese in corn tortillas.
Put cheese and left over chili on top of rolled up tortillas.
Heat until cheese is bubbly, about 15 minutes.

title: biscuit tortoni
directions: Break macaroons into pieces and roll until finely crushed.
Add 1/2 cup crumbs to light cream.
Add sugar and salt; stir until well mixed.
Let soak about 1 hour.
Beat heavy cream until thick, then gradually beat in macaroon mixture.
Add flavorings.
Fill small paper cups with mixture.
Sprinkle on rest of macaroon crumbs. Freeze 3 hours.
Serve.

title: praline squares
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well. Gradually add flour.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Place	drained
peas
in
bottom
of
casserole
dish. Scatter the almonds
on top of the peas.
Add a layer of green beans followed by a layer of undiluted cream of mushroom soup. Place in oven
at
and bake until soup begins to bubble. Remove dish
from
oven and place crumbled French fried onions on top.
Cook	until onions are golden brown.	Sprinkle a dash of paprika on top.

title: mrs. hitt's slap the preacher it's so good banana pudding
directions: Follow package directions for pudding, adding condensed milk and milk.
Using a deep dish bowl, layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding in alternate layers.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs; add carrots, then dry ingredients, drained pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Grease and flour tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for 10 minutes, remove from pan.

title: seafood batter
directions: Mix
well
and	dip seafood in before frying in hot oil until brown.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and store in middle size of 3 piece canister Tupperware canister set.

title: persian bath delight
directions: Steep ingredients in boiling water for thirty minutes.
Strain and add to warm bath water.

title: slime
directions: Place end of popsicle stick in Guar gum, removing what will cling to the tip.
Tap Guar gum into 100 ml of water and stir quickly to avoid lumping.
Should thicken a little.
Add a drop or two of food coloring.
Add Borax solution and stir until gel like. Refrigerate to keep fresh.
And have fun!

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Cook pudding and eggs together with 2 cups of the milk.
Cook according to the directions on the pudding box.
Mix all ingredients well with pudding mixture and churn.

title: cranberry nut pie
directions: Butter an 11-inch pie pan generously.
Add cranberries, then top with nuts.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of sugar on top of cranberries and nuts.
Whisk eggs in a medium bowl until light lemon in color. Add melted butter and sugar while whisking.
Beat in the flour and extract.
Pour batter over cranberries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
It should come out clean or with few crumbs.
Serve hot or cold.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix as listed.
Bake in 8 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl; set aside.
Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes; stir.
Pour mixture over cereal, stirring.
Place powdered sugar into bag.
Pour in cereal.
Shake until coated.

title: angel delight
directions: Mix room temperature cream cheese, sugar, Cool Whip and syrup with electric beater.
Add remaining ingredients with a spatula. Pour into coconut lined pan 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with coconut.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Take from freezer an hour before serving but keep in refrigerator.
Cut into squares. Makes 6 to 10 servings.

title: tasty bread sticks
directions: Pour melted margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Separate biscuits and roll with hands into long thin shapes.
Roll in margarine and set in place in pan.
Sprinkle generously with garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Mix cooked spaghetti, onion, pepper and chopped tomato with seasoning mix.
Pour dressing over and mix well.
Let set overnight.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Mix well dry ingredients, except oat bran.
Add 1 cup vegetable oil, then 4 egg whites; well beaten.
Mix in 1 quart buttermilk and let set a few minutes (10 minutes).
Then add extra cup of oat bran.
Bake in muffin tins with liners for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and fry chopped beef and sausage (drain well). Put back into skillet.
Add sauce, spices, 1 1/2 tablespoons Ramona and 1 1/2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Simmer until thick (about 20 minutes).

title: vegetarian lentils, pasta and rice
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until onion is tender.
Add lentils and saute 1 minute.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Cook 1 minute to blend flavors.
Add broth or water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Cook on low heat for 40 minutes until lentils are tender.
Fold in cooked macaroni, rice, salt and pepper.
Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Debone salmon and place in medium size bowl.
Mash with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
If mixture is loose add a little more flour.
Form into small cakes and fry in vegetable oil until golden brown, flip and brown other side.

title: cottage cheese gelatin salad
directions: Prepare lime gelatin according to directions and let set. Drain pineapple.
In mixing bowl, whip cottage cheese and Cool Whip until light.
Add lightly set lime gelatin and drained crushed pineapple.
Mix and pour into mold or glass and continue to let set in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, garnish with cherries or sliced kiwi and mint leaves.

title: cheesy sausage rounds
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together. Form into balls about ping pong ball size.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet about 1 1/2-inches apart and press down with a fork to about 1/4-inch thickness. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve
warm or at room temperature.
They freeze well.
Just thaw at room temperature or in a preheated 250° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes about 65 to 70 balls.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce
directions: Heat butter and olive oil, reserve 2 tablespoons of this mixture. Add scallions, saute briefly.
Add parsley, oregano, basil, garlic, tomato, salt, pepper and clam juice drained from clams.
Simmer briefly.
Add clams and then keep hot.
Boil spaghetti and drain.
Return to pan in which it was boiled.
Add reserved butter mixture and Parmesan.
Toss.
Add 1/4 sauce to spaghetti, toss again.
Serve with more sauce on top.

title: chinese sausage bites
directions: In a bowl combine sausage, eggs and bread cubes.
Use a teaspoon for amount to form small balls.
In a frying pan cook balls evenly until brown; drain on paper towels.
In a pot mix chili sauce, sugar, vinegar, garlic salt and soy sauce.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place balls in a serving bowl and cover with sauce.
Serve with toothpicks.
Yield: 20 to 25 appetizers.

title: western sandwiches
directions: Spread bread with margarine.
Heat shortening in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until hot.
Cook and stir onion and bell pepper in shortening about 5 minutes or until onion is tender. Beat eggs slightly in medium bowl with fork or hand beater.
Stir in ham, salt and pepper.

title: garlic potato wedges
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Cut each half into 4 wedges.
In 3-quart saucepan, place potato wedges and add enough water to cover.
Bring to a full boil.
Cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender (8 to 12 minutes).
Drain. In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter on oven (5 to 6 minutes). Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add potato wedges; coat both sides with butter mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Turn potatoes and continue baking 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: oriental spinach salad
directions: Chop the peanuts.
Pull the stems from the spinach.
Wash the leaves and tear them into pieces.
Cut the tomatoes in half.
Add tomatoes and onion slices to the spinach.
In a small jar, shake together vinegar, 1/4 teaspoon salt, soy sauce and cayenne until salt dissolves.
Add oil and shake again to combine ingredients. Pour this dressing over the salad and toss well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli blue cheese fettucine
directions: I wanted to make sure to support my many friends and spiritual "guides" at Pine UMC.
Here's my recipe--it's not elegant, but it sure tastes good!
The perfect dish to bring to a potluck or to round out a dinner or brunch.

title: pineapple ham
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Remove skin and excess fat from ham. Leaving a fat layer of 1/4-inch thick, score and place clove in each diamond score.
Place ham in roasting pan on rack.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: You will also need foil.

title: sweet salad
directions: Mix all together and cool.

title: cranberry-orange nut bread(1993 bake-off winner)
directions: Thinly pare and stack peelings of oranges in small piles.
Cut slivers to make 3/4 cup.
Cut oranges in half; squeeze to make 1 1/3 cups juice.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, water and orange slivers in small pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until it boils.
Lower heat; cook for 8 minutes.
Add margarine; stir until melted.
Cool slightly, then add reserved orange juice and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add syrup mixture; stir until blended.
Stir in nuts and cranberries.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely; store in refrigerator.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Sift together the sugar, cornstarch and salt; stir into the beaten egg yolks. Add water gradually.
Add vinegar.
Place pan over hot water and cook until mixture thickens.
Put in pie shell.

title: cherry-bright chocolate brownies
directions: Cream butter or magarine, eggs and sugar in a small bowl. Blend in the corn syrup, Kirsch, almond extract and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder. Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture; blend well.
Stir in cherries and almonds.
Spread in a greased and floured 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan.
Cool in pan; frost, if desired.
Cut into squares.
Garnish with additional cherry
halves, if desired.
Makes 16.

title: tropical ambrosia muffins
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder and set aside.

title: cheesy spoon bread
directions: Mix cornmeal,
salt,
mustard
and pepper together.
Add to milk and cook,
stirring
constantly,
until
mixture thickens. Add cheese; cook and stir until
cheese
melts, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Pour
into
greased baking dish and bake at 350° until puffy and browned, about 45 minutes. This is supposed to serve 12, but is barely enough for our family of 8.
We like it!

title: chicken marsala
directions: Pound meat until 1/4 inch thick.
Season with salt and pepper; coat with flour.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter with oil in large skillet.
Brown cutlets, 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Remove meat.

title: sweet barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Cool.
Pour mixture into blender; process until smooth.
Refrigerate up to one month. Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: heath bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Turn up edges.
Cover with single layer of saltine crackers.
Heat butter and brown sugar to boiling and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake 4 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over hot mixture.
When softened, spread with spatula.
Cool to room temperature.
Freeze. Peel off foil and break in pieces.

title: waldorf souffle salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin with boiling water.
Add cold water, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Beat at low speed until blended.
Freeze 25 minutes or until set firm about 1 inch from side of bowl but still soft.
Beat at medium speed until fluffy. Fold in apples, walnuts and celery.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: mini-pizzas
directions: Press biscuits out flat on a cookie sheet.
Spoon on some tomato sauce.
Sprinkle on some cheese and put some pepperoni on each.
Bake at 300° for about 10 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: seven minute white icing
directions: Place egg whites, sugar, water and corn syrup or cream of tartar in the top of a double boiler and beat until thoroughly blended.
Place these ingredients over rapidly boiling water.
Beat them constantly with a rotary beater or wire whisk for 7 minutes. Remove icing from heat, add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Continue beating until icing is the right consistency to spread.
You may add 1/2 cup chopped nuts, coconut or crushed peppermint candy.

title: barbecued hamburger and spaghetti(have spaghetti cooking while mixing meatballs.)
directions: Mix and pour over hamburger.
Cook 12 ounce package of spaghetti and drain off water.
Add 1 1/2 cups tomato juice and salt to taste.
Pour over hamburger and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: creamy cheesy baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on size. (Don't forget to prick with fork so they won't explode.)
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out potatoes and mash with butter and enough light cream to make fluffy.
Restuff shells and top with cheese and bacon bits.
Return to oven and bake until cheese melts.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Put all together in a pot. Cook until cabbage is done. Salt and pepper to taste. Serve with corn bread.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Blend together all ingredients and form into a ball.
Chill several hours.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Yield 5 cups.

title: brownies
directions: Place all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Add nuts and mix thoroughly.
Bake in 8-inch square pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine yellow cake mix, melted butter/margarine and 1 egg in a large bowl; mix well.
Pat down into an even layer into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased baking pan.

title: cranberry christmas punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in lemonade.
Add cold water and cranberry juice.
Place a molded ice ring in a large punch bowl.
Pour punch in bowl over ice and slowly add ginger ale.

title: apple dumplings
directions: For syrup mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: apricot-glazed ham and sweet potatoes
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot margarine or butter, cook ham steak until browned on both sides.
In a small bowl, mix apricot preserves, lemon juice and cloves.
Spoon over ham steak.
Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Drain yams and cut into large chunks.
Cut green onions diagonally into 1-inch pieces.
Add yams and green onions to skillet, turning to coat with preserve mixture.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until heated through.
Arrange ham and vegetables on platter.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Garnish with sliced cranberries.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry no bake pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Fold in berries.
Pour in crust.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix in a large bowl with hands and shape into small balls the first 4 ingredients.
Melt the chocolate chips and wax in double boiler.
Stir until smooth.
Dip balls and place on wax paper to cool.

title: baked spaghetti pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Cook spaghetti until tender; drain.
Combine tomato sauce, chili powder, oregano, salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix well.
Heat.
Add hamburger and spaghetti. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry the raw rice in fat until brown.
Cook as instructed on package (not quite done).
Saute the onions in 2 tablespoons fat (oil).
Mix with tomatoes and peppers; add pimento.
Add all the rice.
Mix well.
Season to taste.
Place in greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bernie's cranberry relish
directions: Grind fruits (or process coarsely).
Add sugar, hot water and Jell-O.
Chill.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Layer 1/2 can of beans, 1/2 sour cream, grated cheese and 1/2 of salsa.
Combine avocado, tomato and lemon juice.
Layer over salsa.
Continue to layer beans, sour cream and cheese.
Top with salsa.

title: beef or chicken enchiladas
directions: Use mixer and mix first 5 ingredients together.
Brown ground beef with garlic; drain.
Heat corn tortillas 5 at a time in microwave for about 1 minute.
Pour part of sauce mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Take a tortilla, put some meat mixture in and roll up.
Then cover with rest of sauce.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
I usually do around 24 enchiladas with this recipe.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Scald in soda water; drain and add fresh water.
Cook 15 minutes.
Put in baking dish; add other ingredients.
Cover with water.
Bake for 4 to 5 hours at 350°. Remove cover last half hour.

title: whitewater gourmet fried trout
directions: Thaw trout if frozen.
Season lightly with salt and pepper; coat with flour.
Fry in 2 tablespoons butter for 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Remove to platter and keep warm.
Add remaining butter to skillet.
Saute mushrooms and green onions until tender. Stir in lemon juice and vermouth.
Pour over trout.
Serves 2.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Make mush with water and cornmeal and line 9-inch square pan with 2-inch layer of mush.
Fry onion in oil until pale yellow; add meat and brown lightly.
Add tomatoes, garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into pan and top with remaining mush.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: hamburger dressing big mac style
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve on hamburgers instead of mustard or mayonnaise.

title: robert redford cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake as directed on box. Cool cake 5 minutes. Poke many holes in cake with end of wooden spoon, stretching the holes as you go. Pour ice cream topping into each hole and cover the cake.
Use as much as you want. Should use entire bottle. Refrigerate cake until cooled. Spread Cool Whip on top of cake (thick). Sprinkle with butterscotch chips. Refrigerate.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and put all in crock-pot. Cook about 4 to 6 hours.
I start mine on high; after it's good and hot, I turn it down to low and let it cook.
It can be cooked on high the entire time.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and rinse in cold water.

In a large bowl, combine everything but the tomatoes, olives, broccoli and cheese. Cover and refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours for flavors to blend. Before serving, add the tomatoes, broccoli and olives and toss; sprinkle with cheese.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Separate 1 egg, saving yolk for frosting.
Add the egg white to 1 whole egg.
Beat well.
Blend milk, vanilla, brown sugar, peanut butter and melted butter.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture, stirring well.

title: chili
directions: Sprinkle hamburger with salt and pepper to taste.
Chop onions and add to meat.
Brown hamburger and onions in pan.
When browned, add chili powder and tomato juice.
Put in double boiler and simmer for approximately 30 minutes.

title: peach pie filling fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together and then mix peach pie filling with fruit.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: bacon burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon and shape into 12 patties.
Wrap with slice of bacon; fasten ends with toothpick. Place on broiler rack 3 inches from heat and broil 5 minutes. Turn and broil another 5 minutes.

title: any day cheese ball
directions: Beat together all ingredients except nuts.
Shape into a ball. Roll in walnuts.
Wrap with wax paper.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes one large ball.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Then add corn. Mix; drop by tablespoon into hot oil and deep-fry until brown. Serve hot. To be served with a meal.

title: swedish oven-pancake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with milk using an egg beater. Grease 9 x 12 glass pan with 1 teaspoon of butter.
Pour mixture in and bake at 425 degrees for 45 -50 minutes, until golden brown. Serve with maple syrup and sausage or bacon.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole with a few cracker crumbs.
Rotate layers of asparagus, cheese, cracker crumbs, butter and almonds. Pour milk in side.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together while hot.
Add drained oranges.
Put in mold and refrigerate.

title: savory beef stew
directions: Place frozen stew vegetables and water in large microwave-safe casserole dish.
Cover and cook on high for 12 to 14 minutes, or until vegetables are cooked through.
Stir in Beef Tips with Gravy and ketchup.
Cover and return to microwave.
Heat 8 minutes, or until warmed thoroughly.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots; drain and let cool.
Slice onion and pepper in rings.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours or longer.
These will keep at least 2 weeks.

title: mother's brown rolls
directions: Bring water and salt to boil; stir in Moltex.
When it bubbles up good, remove and stir in margarine, molasses and sugar.
Beat eggs and add.
In large mixing pan, sprinkle yeast into 1 cup good warm water.
When cereal mixture is lukewarm, combine with yeast and 2 cups flour until well mixed.
Add about 8 more cups flour. Turn out and knead for 5 minutes.
Return to bowl; cover and let rise.
Make into good sized rolls and place in greased pans. Cover; let rise until doubled.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 28 minutes, no more.
Turn out on wire racks and grease tops with butter.
Makes about 5 dozen rolls.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 400° oven until inserted knife comes out clean, about 1 hour.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Note:
Add a little red food coloring for color.

title: colcannon
directions: Clean, pare and quarter potatoes.
Cook in unsalted water for about 15 minutes, or until tender.
While potatoes are cooking, melt butter in saucepan.
Add cabbage and scallions.
Cover; cook over low heat until tender, about 5 or 10 minutes.
When potatoes are done, drain well and mash.
Gradually add hot milk; beat until fluffy.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste, mixing well.
Add cabbage and scallions to mashed potatoes; turn into serving dish. Makes 6 servings.

title: ian's gastronomically good gwock-uh-moley
directions: Welcome to the world of guacamole cuisine.
You are congratulated on the epicurean adventure on which you are about to embark.
Get all of your ingredients in order and prepare to prepare a simple, awesomely wonderful and even edible delight.
So let's get started!

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburg, bacon and onion; then add other ingredients and bake at 375° until done.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Put in large bowl and mix well. Store in tightly covered container. Use 2 tsp. per cup of boiling water.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: low calorie fruit dip
directions: Put fruit on toothpicks; chill.
Mix other ingredients together.
Dip fruit into mixture.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In medium bowl, combine Bisquick, cornmeal and water; mix well.
With floured hands, pat dough up bottom and sides of greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
In skillet or microwave, brown meat with onion.
Pour off grease.
Stir in tomato sauce, bouillon and chili powder.
Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Spread beans over baked crust.
Spoon meat mixture over beans.
Top with cheese; bake for 10 to 20 minutes, until heated through.
Garnish with tomatoes, lettuce and olives.

title: enchiladas(chili colorado)
directions: Brown flour in oil as for gravy.
Add all water at once stirring rapidly.
Continue stirring until gravy thickens.
(If it is lumpy you can run it through a strainer).
Add all remaining ingredients except tortillas, onion, olives, and cheese.
Simmer for 15-20 minutes.
Add water if too thick.
Fry tortillas in oil for 10 seconds.
Stack them in a 13 x 9 inch casserole dish while you fry them all.
Stuff and roll each tortilla with cheese, olives and onion.
Pour sauce over the top and heat in oven or microwave until the cheese melts.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sift powdered sugar to get lumps out.
1/3 of mix to 1 c. hot water for great hot chocolate.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Beat egg and sugar, shortening, milk and vanilla.
Add cocoa, flour and baking powder which have been sifted together; then add nuts.
Drop by spoonful on greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes or more.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add bananas. Sift dry ingredients.
Add nuts; blend well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, leaving center lower.
Let stand 20 minutes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: tangy tuna macaroni
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
