Pour all ingredients into greased casserole.
Toss together.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and melted margarine around border of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
In a large 3-quart casserole dish, crush Doritos chips slightly. Add the onion, green chilies and chicken.
In a large saucepan, add soups, spice, chicken broth and Tabasco sauce.
Mix well. Bring to a boil and pour over the chicken-chip mixture in casserole dish.
Mix well. Grate cheese and put over top.
Sprinkle with chili powder. Bake at 350° only long enough to melt cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup and sour cream together and place in baking dish.
Mix Ritz crackers and oleo together and sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Top with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: caramel corn and nuts
directions: Pop corn and put in a large pan.
Boil butter, sugar, corn syrup, flavorings, salt, pecans and peanuts for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the soda and cream of tartar.
Stir and pour over the popped corn.
Mix well and spread on jelly roll pans. Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir frequently during baking.
Remove corn and nuts from pans onto waxed paper and separate each piece. Allow to cool completely before storing in airtight containers.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise. Scoop out insides, leaving a thin shell.
With electric mixer, mash potatoes with butter, salt, pepper, sour cream and chives. Beat until light and fluffy.
Spoon into shells and top with cheese.
Bake in shallow baking dish until cheese melts, approximately 10 minutes at 350°.

title: ham casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Toss to mix well.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet beans and sausage
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook sausage until browned and cooked through, about 10 minutes.
Discard all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add onions and cook, stirring often until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, molasses, mustard and vinegar; mix well.
Stir in peas and beans, cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown onion, ground beef and a little salt and pepper.
Drain grease.
Combine meat mixture with green beans and mushroom soup. Spread evenly in baking dish.
Place Tater Tots on top, covering meat mixture completely.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 425°.

title: seafood medley
directions: Combine tuna, crabmeat, and shrimp in bowl.
Stir in French dressing; refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Add celery, cucumber, radishes and capers to seafood mixture.
Blend lemon juice with mayo in small bowl.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Toss seafood mixture with seasoned mayo.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 5 - 6.

title: polish mashed potato topper
directions: Combine ingredients. Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer for about 1/2 hour. Pour over mashed potatoes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box; drain well.
Add Cheez Whiz to drained macaroni;
stir until cheese is melted.
Grate cheese in large dish, then take large baking dish and put layer of grated cheese on bottom.
Add layer of macaroni; then layer of cheese,
continue
to
layer.
End
with topping of cheese. Beat eggs
well
in
dish;
add
milk
to eggs, then pour over macaroni and cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until set in center.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Mix both boxes of vanilla pudding with 3 cups of milk. Slice bananas in bowl. Add pineapple. Stir to coat bananas with juice. Add sliced strawberries. Set aside. In bottom of dish, pinch cake up in bite-size pieces. Drain fruit in colander. Put fruit over cake. Next spread vanilla pudding on top of fruit. Top with Cool Whip. Let set a couple of hours in refrigerator.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grate
cheese
and mix well with
cracker
crumbs.
Add liquid from asparagus to soup.
Put layer of crumbs and cheese in bottom of buttered casserole dish, layer
of
asparagus and sprinkle
on nuts.
Cover with soup.
Repeat.
Put
layer
of crumbs and cheese on top.
Dot all layers with margarine. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Can be prepared the day before.

title: smoked fish spread
directions: Remove smoked fish flesh from bones and skin.
Place in salad bowl and flake with fork.
Add chopped vegetables and pickle. Stir in mayonnaise.
Serve on party crackers as Hors D'Oeuvres or use to enhance salads.

title: corn custard pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or processor on high speed 30 seconds.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole (ungreased).
Place in pan of water.
Water should come about halfway up the outside of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: drum major cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into shortening, sugar and egg mixture. Chill dough and roll into balls size of walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies that travel well and stand up to any competition.

title: oatmeal rolls
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients and let cool until lukewarm. Add sugars, salt and yeast. Add flour and knead well. Let rise until double. Form rolls and let rise approximately 25 minutes and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Soak tops with butter after removal from oven.

title: anna's sweet blueberry muffins
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Sprinkle blueberries with a small amount of flour.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Beat egg with a wire whisk; add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add butter and milk and mix well. Add this mixture to the flour mixture.
Fold the flour in, then add the blueberries.
Drop by spoonfuls into a buttered muffin tin and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 large muffins or up to 24 small muffins.

title: rice and peas italian style(risi e bisi)
directions: Melt butter. Add onion and saut until soft, not golden brown. Stir in rice and saut until all rice is coated, about 2 minutes.
Add stock and wine; bring to a boil. Cover and reduce to low. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until rice is tender, but firm to the bite and most liquid has been absorbed, about 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Pour oil in a large saucepan.
Stir-fry potato, onion, tomato and jalapeno.
Add water, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; stir in cheese half through cooking.
Soup is done when potatoes are tender.

title: chicken broccoli fettuccine
directions: In a skillet in hot margarine, cook garlic 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup, milk, cheeses and onion.
Add chicken and broccoli.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring often. Toss with fettuccine and serve.

title: texas dessert
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving to improve flavor.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients; add zucchini.
Mix again.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: fruit punch
directions: One day ahead make Kool-Aid and put in small round cups; freeze.
Day to be used, mix all together in large bowl and serve.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat; add all other ingredients except potatoes and cook 45 minutes, then add potatoes and cook 10 minutes more, until potatoes are done.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, onion, peppers, lemon juice and hot sauce; mix well. Spread thin layer of mixture over individual tortilla shells and roll up. Secure with toothpick and refrigerate until right before serving. Cut into bite-size pieces and secure with toothpick. Arrange on plate and serve with bowl of picante sauce.

title: walnut raisin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Brown sausage and drain.
Cut up onion and chop celery; add instant chicken noodle soup, water and mushrooms.
Stir in the sausage and rice.
Place in large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Can top with Ritz cracker crumbs before baking.

title: raisin apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Combine egg, milk and oil and stir into dry ingredients until just moistened. Fold in apples and raisins. Pour batter into prepared muffin pan and then make Topping.

title: fridge or freezer jam
directions: Mix zucchini, onion, salt, basil and pepper in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High until zucchini is tender-crisp, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes; stir.
Place tomato slices on zucchini.
Mix sour cream and cheese; spread over tomato slices.
Sprinkle with dried basil.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on Medium-low (40%) until tomato slices are warm, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: no-bake orange balls
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Roll balls in shredded coconut.

title: barbecued tuna
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and Karo syrup.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling, stirring occasionally, about 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture turns light caramel color (290°); stir in vanilla.
Pour syrup over popped corn and nuts on baking sheet; toss with two large spoons until popcorn and nuts are coated.
Spread out to dry.
Break apart and store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: angel food cake
directions: Leave egg whites at room temperature.
Sift powdered sugar and flour together 3 times.
In large bowl, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Sift 1/4 of flour mixture over egg whites.
Fold in gently.
Repeat, folding remaining flour mixture.
Pour into ungreased tube pan. Bake on lowest rack at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes (until top springs back).
Remove from oven and immediately invert pan (turn upside down on small neck bottle to cool).
Cool thoroughly.
Loosen side of cake from pan and remove.

title: 7-layered salad
directions: Place all of the lettuce on the bottom of a large salad bowl. Place a layer of all the green peppers on top of the lettuce, followed by all the onions and all the peas.

title: spinach dip in bread mound
directions: Mix and chill all ingredients 2 or more hours.
Cut off top of large round French bread.
Hollow out, cutting bread into cubes or chunks for dipping.
Fill hollowed out bread with spinach dip. Surround with cut up bread or veggies.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir in egg.
Add to milk mixture.
Add flour.
Stir until well blended.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: the malone family brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and butter over medium-low heat in saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes according to desired moistness.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut up potatoes; dice up onion, celery and garlic.
Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter/margarine.
Add potatoes and just enough water to cover potatoes.
Add parsley, bay leaves and basil.
Cook on low heat until potatoes are soft enough to mash. Remove from stove and cream potatoes; thin with Carnation cream and milk (add more if needed).
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Beat egg white with 1 tablespoon water. Mix the 3 dry ingredients.
Roll nuts in mixture and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool and store in refrigerator.

title: medium white sauce
directions: Melt butter; add flour and blend. Add milk and cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly. Add 1/4 teaspoon salt.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Mix and knead together the flour, oil, water and salt.
Press evenly into pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake crust for about 15 minutes before placing ingredients on top.

title: irish dirt cake
directions: Break Oreos into crumbs.
Cream together sugar, butter and cream cheese. Add pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Blend until creamy. Add all but 1 cup Oreos.
Spoon into cups.
Top with Oreo cookie dirt.

title: new american pot roast
directions: In a heavy Dutch oven or casserole, brown meat on all sides in oil.
Sprinkle with garlic after browning.
Add sliced carrots and onions to pan.
Place around meat.
Add beef broth.
Cover with lid.
Cook meat in oven at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat and place on a platter.
Lift onions and carrots onto meat.
Cover.
Keep warm.
Strain remaining juices from pan.
Pour into small saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer until reduced to half the original volume.
Add salt to taste. Whisk in mustard and whisk constantly until sauce is heated through.
Slice meat.
Serve with sauce or your favorite gravy. Makes four servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Lay cut-up chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat soups, rice and milk together.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dry onion soup on top.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Add your favorite toppings.

title: keftethes(greek fried meatballs)
directions: Brown onions in a little oil.
Place onions in a mixing bowl and add meat, bread crumbs, eggs and seasonings.
Blend well and shape into desired size.
Roll lightly in flour and fry in very hot oil.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl and beat the tar out of it. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oil and margarine until smooth.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Add powdered sugar and regular sugar.
Beat in eggs. Add flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with bottom of glass which has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Combine hamburger, mango, onions and oil; cook until well done.
Add tomatoes, corn, chili powder and salt.
Prepare cornbread mix as directed on package.
Mix into above mixture. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cut up fruit in a bowl.
In another bowl, beat 4 egg yolks and milk.
Pour into double boiler and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in marshmallows and cool in refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients; stir in hot water until dissolved.
Pour in milk and stir.
Cook on high, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: meatballs with mushroom gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup.
Roll into balls, then roll in flour and fry until brown.
Put into baking dish.
Combine soup and 1/2 can to 1 can of water; pour over meatballs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 40 minutes or until gravy forms.

title: gayla's hot apple cider
directions: Boil for 2 minutes and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: shrimp in garlic
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Stir in garlic, bay leaves and Tabasco.
When garlic sizzles, add shrimp and parsley, stirring constantly, until shrimp are pink, about 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serve with pasta or rice and French bread.

title: ilene's hot spiced teawestboro, missouri
directions: Steep an hour and strain above ingredients.

title: amish cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: emily's honey milk surprise(created at age 6)
directions: Then bake for 3 seconds in microwave.

title: fruit cocktail ice pops
directions: You will also need 12 popsicle molds or 12 paper cups (3 ounces each) and 12 popsicle sticks.

title: quick pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables and cream of chicken soup.
Pour into one pie crust.
Invert other pie crust on top.
Bake for temperature and time limit on pie crust.

title: granny's sunflower white cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening together.
Add vanilla and milk; beat vigorously 200 strokes or two minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Add egg whites and continue beating two more minutes, scraping bowl often.
Batter will be thin.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cover with favorite icing and enjoy.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Serve on toasted bread or crackers.
Yields 1 2/3 cups.

title: barbecue kolbassi
directions: Boil your kolbassi 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool so you can handle and slice very thin.
Mix your sugar, ketchup and water.
Pour over kolbassi and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
You can also use for chipped, chopped ham.

title: beef casserole
directions: Layer vegetables and meat in a casserole.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/2 cup water and juice from peas.
Pour over meat.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: luscious lemon cake
directions: Prepare, bake and cool cake following package directions in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Split cake in half horizontally.
Combine lemonade concentrate and condensed milk in medium bowl; fold in whipped topping.
Add yellow coloring, if desired.

title: best blueberry pie
directions: Set oven to 425°.
In medium bowl combine dry ingredients. Toss in blueberries.
Pour in pie crust.
Cut up 2 tablespoons butter into small pieces and dot all over pie.
Squeeze fresh lemon juice over pie.
Put on top crust.
Cut slits and sprinkle or dust top crust with sugar.
Cover crust edges with tinfoil and remove last 15 minutes of baking to prevent overbrowning.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw bread and let rise.
Roll into rectangle shape.
Layer sausage, onion, pepper and cheese.
Fold over ends; roll and seal. Let rise until double in size on greased baking sheet.
Brush top with beaten egg yolk.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream in large bowl the sugars, cooking oil, eggs and vanilla. Thoroughly mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir once when cheese and butter melt.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil and pumpkin; mix well.
Add 3/4 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 2 (5 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch) or 3 loaf pans.

title: bacon stuffed burgers
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and discard all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Saute onion in drippings until tender. Crumble bacon and add with mushrooms to skillet.
Set aside. Then, combine ground beef, sausage, cheese, pepper, garlic powder and steak sauce.
Shape into 16 patties.
Divide bacon mixture and place on top of 8 of the patties.

title: chinese style chicken wings
directions: Melt butter.
Add soy sauce and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Cool. Cover chicken with marinade.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight, being sure all pieces are well covered.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in marinade.
Grill to brown, brushing chicken with marinade.

title: pizza pull aparts
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters and place in a 13 x 9 pan. Place meat on top of biscuits and pour pizza sauce over meat.
Put on toppings and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes or until biscuits are cooked through.
Take out pieces with fork.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken pieces.
Fry in butter or margarine until lightly browned.
Cook in pressure cooker 20 minutes or in a slow cooker overnight on low.
Add 1/4 cup catsup and 1/2 cup water, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar to chicken in cooker.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add vegetables and simmer until tender.
Blend flour with milk.
Stir into broth mixture. Cook and stir over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Stir in chicken, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Spoon into a 10-inch casserole.
Place crust over filling in casserole.
Seal edges. Make slits in crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is golden.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a greased 2-quart casserole, ending with crackers.
Drizzle with melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bishop's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add tomato sauce, paste and ragu sauce.
Simmer for one hour.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Lay noodles in an oblong dish.
Layer noodles, sauce mixture, cheese and sour cream.
Bake at 350 degrees until cheese is melted.

title: cheese fries(lighter eating - 2 points)
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1/2 inch thick strips. Preheat oven to 400°. Coat a large baking sheet with cooking spray. Arrange potatoes on prepared baking sheet and season to taste with salt and pepper. Bake until golden brown and fork-tender, about 40 minutes. Move potatoes so that they are closer together on baking sheet; top with cheese. Bake until cheese melts, about 5 minutes more.

title: broccoli rice bake
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Stir in rice, soup and broccoli.
Put in a buttered shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put back in oven until melted.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Simmer all ingredients together in large pot for 5 hours.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles.

title: muncey's old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add soda dissolved in vinegar.
Add flour gradually to make a stiff batter that can be rolled very thin.
Cut out and bake in a moderate oven until brown, about 8 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed. Mix eggs, pimentos, cheese, mayonnaise and soup together. Place layer of broccoli, layer of sauce and layer of bread crumbs. Repeat. Put pats of butter on top. Bake about 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: strawberry dessert salad(frozen)
directions: Melt marshmallows in top of double boiler with strawberry juice; cool.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Blend cream cheese until creamy.
Add salad dressing and whipped cream; combine with strawberry mixture.
Pour into dish and freeze until firm.
Cut into squares and arrange on lettuce leaves.
Top with whipped cream and a whole frozen strawberry.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Mix water, salt, pepper and cheese. After cheese has melted, add cream and cornstarch mixture. Then add broccoli.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: In a large electric skillet fry bacon until crisp.
Set bacon aside.
Fry eggs on both sides in bacon drippings left in skillet. Shred egg and set aside.
Brown onion and rice in bacon grease. Add shrimp and remaining ingredients; stir well until thoroughly heated, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in broken pieces of bacon and shredded egg.
Serves about 6.

title: microwave chicken
directions: Wash chicken; drain.
Sprinkle both sides of chicken with seasoned salt.
Coat with cracker crumbs and put in covered casserole dish.
Bake on High for 25 minutes.

title: country rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water for 10 minutes.
Combine shortening, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Add hot milk and stir to soften shortening.
Let cool to lukewarm; add egg and dissolved yeast and beat with electric beater.
Gradually beat in flour, 1 cup at a time, until dough is soft.
Grease a 3-quart size bowl; place roll in and grease.
Roll top.
Cover with clean cloth.
Set in a warm place to rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Pinch off into small balls.
Place in greased muffin tins.
Cover; let rise for 1 hour.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Garnish with chopped nuts.
May add cottage cheese, coconut or marshmallows.
Chill.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Stir ground beef in pan until browned.
Drain off excess fat. Add chili, onion, catsup to taste, salt and pepper to taste. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Mix as any cookies but shape into rolls.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Slice and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt chips into top of double boiler.
Add Eagle Brand milk, coconut and nuts.
Mix well. Pour into graham cracker crust and chill until firm.

title: breakfast bars
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and fruit.
(I put the cereal and raisins in a big bowl and pour the heated mixture over them.)
Press into 9 x 13 pan that has been sprayed with Pam or buttered.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in above order.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Frost with vanilla or cream frosting.

title: beets in ginger vinaigrette
directions: Drain and quarter beets. Slice scallions. In medium bowl, stir together vinegar, ginger, garlic, lemon zest and juice, honey, salt and pepper until salt dissolves. Gradually beat in oil until mixture thickens. In large bowl, combine lettuce greens with half of dressing. Transfer to platter.
In same bowl, combine beets, scallions and remaining dressing. Serve over greens.

title: creole style lima beans
directions: Soak limas overnight.
Cook until tender.
Cook pepper and onion in butter for few minutes.
Thoroughly blend in flour; add tomatoes gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add seasoning.
Pour over limas and cook 15 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix the flour, salt and sugar.
Add eggs and pineapple.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with cubes of bread and top with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and pumpkin well.
Add egg and mix well. Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon onto cookie sheet (sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Place on wire rack to cool, then ice each cookie with icing.

title: crock-pot saucy steak dinner
directions: Place strips of steak in pot. Add onions, celery and mushrooms. In a small bowl, combine dressing, sour cream mix, water, Worcestershire sauce and mushroom liquid. Pour over mixture in pot. Cover pot. Simmer at medium setting for 5 to 6 hours. Keep warm on low setting. Serve over noodles. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: gourmet cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skin. Peel and shred coarsely.
Combine in a saucepan the cheese and 1/4 cup butter. Stir until melted. Blend sour cream or milk, onion and seasoning.
Fold in potatoes and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle paprika over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain grease.
Spread bread cubes in buttered pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Top with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Beat well and pour over sausage and cheese. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Remove foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread coconut in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, lightly greased. Spread pecans over coconut.
Mix cake mix as directed on box and pour over pecans.
Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Drop spoonfuls over cake mix.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water for 5 minutes.
Beat egg yolks.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, pumpkin, salt, spices and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickens.
Add gelatin to mixture; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Beat in remaining sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Fold gently the pumpkin and egg mixture together.
Pour into cooked pie shell until firm from chilling in the refrigerator.
Makes 1 pie.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Soften margarine; add rest of ingredients.
Spread mixture on both sides of rolls.
Put ham and cheese on rolls.
Warm at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: gnocchis(homemade italian pasta)
directions: Pour all ingredients onto cutting board.
Mix well with hands. Roll into 2 separate dough balls.
Cut each dough ball into 1-inch sections.
Roll each 1-inch section into a coil.
Cut each coil into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll each ball on the tip of a fork to decorate.
Lay each decorated noodle on a piece of wax paper. Place in freezer until frozen.
Once frozen, boil until noodles float to top.

title: chicken breasts(boneless and skinless)
directions: Cover chicken breasts with mustard and dip in bread crumbs to coat.
Put in pan to fit.
Pour white wine in pan around chicken, about 1/2-inch deep.
Cut tomatoes in half and squeeze out seeds, then cut tomatoes in small pieces and add to chicken in pan. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour. Remove chicken from pan and keep warm.
Add 1 chicken bouillon cube to cup of boiling water and dissolve.
Add flour to pan juices to thicken, then bouillon to make gravy.
Serve with rice.

title: hot crab and shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: c.m.p.  dessert
directions: Mix and spread over cream cheese mixture.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks slightly; add 3/4 cup sugar, pumpkin, milk, salt and spices.
Put in double boiler and cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in soaked gelatin until it is dissolved.
Cool.
Whip egg whites with 1/3 teaspoon salt until stiff, beating in the remainder (3/4 cup) sugar.
When pumpkin begins to set, fold in egg white mixture.
Fill pie crust.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: fat-free coffee frosting
directions: Combine brown sugar, water and cream of tartar in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook, over medium heat, stirring often, until mixture begins to boil and sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking and stirring often, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (240° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Add coffee granules, stirring until dissolved.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients.
Wash and cut chicken wings.
Soak overnight in sauce in large Ziploc bag.
Place broiler rack 7 inches from heat.
Broil for 10 minutes on each side.
After browned, turn oven down to 350° and bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream the soft butter with the sugar. Add the eggs.
Dust a little flour over fruits and nuts.
Leave fruits and nuts uncut, except pineapple.
Add flour.
Bake in greased tube pans lined with brown paper for 3 hours at 275°.
This makes 10 pounds of cake or enough for two 10-inch pans.
Leave cakes out 2 or 3 days before storing. Baste occasionally with additional brandy or sherry.
Store in covered containers.
Keeps well for months.

title: betty's cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo in heavy pan, then add butter flavoring and nuts.
Stir until nuts are well coated.
Mix sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla together.
Stir only until blended; do not beat.
Add to chocolate mixture, put in cupcake pan and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: southern pork chops
directions: Brown chops quickly on both sides in small amount of oil. Pour off excess fat and return to pan.
Pour soup and milk mixture over pork chops with sliced onions.
Cover and cook over very low heat for about 5 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: easy plain cake
directions: Mix well and bake 30 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, peppers, onion and sugar and stir and chill for 2 hours.
Bring vinegar, oil, salt and poppy seed to a boil. Stir until salt dissolves.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Stir gently; cover and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: chicken copenhagan
directions: Butter 13 x 8 x 1 3/4-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour and spread uncooked rice; add hot water and salt.
Place chicken pieces over rice; dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika; cover with soup and sprinkle with almonds.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Cut apples in quarters. Wrap in crescent rolls, starting at large end first. Place in baking dish. Mix orange juice, sugar and margarine together. Pour over wrapped apples. Bake at 350° until brown. Baste several times while baking.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in blender or mixer.
Freeze in muffin cups or liners.
(I use Dixie cups.)
May be served on lettuce leaves.
Serves 24.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Mix milk, corn bread mix and sugar. Set aside. Brown beef and onion.
Add soup, water and seasonings.
Mix and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour into large skillet or 9-inch baking dish. Top with corn bread batter and bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yields 4 generous servings.

title: deluxe pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Pour batter into 2 (9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans that have been lined with heavy brown paper and thoroughly buttered.

Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from oven and allow to stand 10 minutes, then remove from pan and carefully strip off paper.
Cool on rack.
Makes 2 loaf cakes.

title: grandma's copper penny carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until just tender.
Set aside to cool.
Cut green pepper into rings.
Alternate carrots, pepper and onion in dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat until blended.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
Use as relish or hors d'oeuvre.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients, beat well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour in a deep casserole dish.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine water and sugar and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into small paper cups and freeze.
Serve slightly thawed.

title: candied yams
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets in water to cover until tender.
Drain, peel and slice.
Arrange slices in a casserole dish, add a syrup made of the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate-mint snow-top cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Over hot water, melt 1 cup of morsels.
In bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add melted morsels and vanilla.
Beat eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup of morsels.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap.
Freeze until firm.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Coat with confectioners sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy praline patties
directions: Combine sugar and soda; stir in cream carefully. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat; cook and stir to soft-ball stage. Use both thermometer and cold water test.
Remove from heat; add butter immediately. Add pecans. Beat mixture until thick, 2 to 3 minutes. Drop from metal spoon onto waxed paper. If necessary, add a little hot water. Yield: 24 to 30 patties.

title: basic bannock bread
directions: Mix ingredients with a few tablespoons of water.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in covered oven.
The dough can bake as one large loaf or several small ones.
Serves 8.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from the mushrooms. Chop stems finely. Reserve caps. Place stems in paper towel and squeeze to remove any liquid.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick margarine (melted). Place in oblong pan and put in freezer to cool.
Mix confectioners sugar, eggs and 1 stick melted margarine with mixer and beat for 10 minutes.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Slice bananas and sprinkle with lemon juice to keep from turning dark.
Place on top of mixture, then place the can of drained crushed pineapple on top.
Spread 12 ounce bowl of Cool Whip on top, then place cherries and nuts on top of Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin bread ring
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add water, eggs and pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to liquid ingredients. Mix until smooth.
Place 2-inch diameter glass in center of waxed paper lined 2-quart glass casserole to form ring mold.
(Be sure waxed paper remains flat in dish.)
Pour batter into dish.
Cook on High for 8 to 9 minutes or until top springs back when lightly pressed with finger.
(You may want to turn dish halfway through cooking time.)
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove glass and invert ring on serving platter.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, butter and milk. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Remove from heat.

title: party mix
directions: Combine cereal and nuts in large roaster.
Mix butter and seasoning.
Bake 2 hours at 250°.
Stir occasionally.
Store in airtight container.

title: orange salad
directions: Fold all ingredients
together and chill until ready to serve. (Jell-O is mixed in dry.)

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tests done.

title: brownies
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar, salt and eggs together.
Melt chocolate over hot water.
When melted, add with vanilla to first mixture. Add flour and walnuts; stir until smooth.
Spread batter into a layer 1/2-inch thick in a square pan which has been rubbed with Crisco.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) until brown, about 25 minutes.

title: trim slim custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium size bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add Equal and vanilla.

Slowly stir in scalded milk. Pour into two 1-cup custard cups. Set in shallow pan filled with 1-inch of hot water. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Contains 150 calories per 3/4 cup. Serves 2.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Pour asparagus into dish; add cream of mushroom soup and mix.
Crush crackers over the soup mix.
Bake until the crackers are browned. Top with the cheese and bake until cheese melts.
You may add extra cheese.

title: cheesy chili rellenos
directions: Rinse chiles; remove seeds and pat dry.
Stuff chiles with strips of cheese.
(If chiles tear, overlap torn sides; batter will hold them together.)
Beat the egg yolks with an electric mixer until fluffy and pale yellow (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Add 3 tablespoons flour, water and salt; mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into yolk mixture.
Dredge stuffed chiles in flour, coating well.
Dip chiles in egg mixture.
Brown chiles on both sides in 1/2 inch of oil at 370° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: crunchy chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce cups or use for sandwiches.
Yields 12 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Crush Product 19 cereal to measure 1/2 cup.
Stir together cereal, flour, cinnamon and brown sugar, mixing until crumbly.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lay out crescent roll dough and press perforations to seal.
Mix cream cheese, mushrooms, onions and salt.
Spread over dough.
Roll up in jelly roll fashion and slice into 1-inch pieces.
Brush with egg; sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yield:

title: baked ziti, new jersey style
directions: Mix ziti, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, egg, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups sauce in a 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dish; spread 1/2 cup sauce, then macaroni mixture.
Top with the remaining sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Wait 10 minutes and cut into squares.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together and chill until ready to serve.
